1
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:57,015
-They've broken through the front lines!
-I've lost contact with the capital!

2
00:00:57,099 --> 00:00:58,141
There's too many of them!

3
00:00:58,934 --> 00:01:00,310
[explosions]

4
00:01:00,686 --> 00:01:01,979
Stand fast! [grunts]

5
00:01:05,190 --> 00:01:07,067
[Decepticon 1] Finish them! [grunts]

6
00:01:08,986 --> 00:01:10,070
[Optimus grunts]

7
00:01:14,449 --> 00:01:15,492
[Optimus grunts]

8
00:01:17,536 --> 00:01:19,496
Where's B-127?

9
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:28,255
[Decepticon screams]

10
00:01:33,302 --> 00:01:34,970
[Bumblebee] Sorry I'm late.
I hit a little traffic.

11
00:01:35,053 --> 00:01:36,930
[Autobot 1] Get down! Incoming!

12
00:01:37,014 --> 00:01:38,599
[Bumblebee] Uh, Optimus.

13
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:44,229
[Decepticon 2] Decepticons, attack!

14
00:01:44,313 --> 00:01:46,148
Autobots, fall back!

15
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:48,358
Get to the tower!

16
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:50,944
[Decepticon 3] Destroy the launch pad!

17
00:01:51,153 --> 00:01:52,988
Let none escape!

18
00:01:59,119 --> 00:02:01,038
[Optimus] Cybertron has fallen.

19
00:02:01,246 --> 00:02:03,040
Get to the escape pods.

20
00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:06,043
There are other Autobots
scattered across the galaxy.

21
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:08,462
We must reach them if we hope to survive.

22
00:02:08,545 --> 00:02:11,131
Optimus, this is our home.
We have to fight for it.

23
00:02:17,012 --> 00:02:18,639
We will fight on.

24
00:02:18,764 --> 00:02:20,849
But we must find refuge first.

25
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:23,226
I found a planet that's well hidden.

26
00:02:23,393 --> 00:02:24,436
Earth.

27
00:02:24,519 --> 00:02:27,356
You will travel there
and establish a base for us.

28
00:02:27,439 --> 00:02:30,108
Once we've gathered the others,
we'll join you.

29
00:02:30,275 --> 00:02:32,110
You must protect the planet.

30
00:02:32,361 --> 00:02:34,112
If the Decepticons find it,

31
00:02:34,321 --> 00:02:36,948
then our people are truly finished.

32
00:02:37,032 --> 00:02:38,241
Now go!

33
00:02:53,799 --> 00:02:55,342
Good luck, soldier.

34
00:02:55,467 --> 00:02:56,968
I'll buy you some time.

35
00:02:58,637 --> 00:02:59,596
[grunts]

36
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:05,268
[panting]

37
00:03:05,352 --> 00:03:06,436
[grunts]

38
00:03:54,317 --> 00:03:55,610
[screaming]

39
00:03:55,736 --> 00:03:56,987
[all grunting]

40
00:04:00,323 --> 00:04:02,325
No! Ow! Ow! Ow!

41
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:05,412
Okay, okay! I'm dead already, man!

42
00:04:06,997 --> 00:04:08,832
[scoffs] Oh, not just you.

43
00:04:09,124 --> 00:04:10,417
Being the overachiever that you are,

44
00:04:10,584 --> 00:04:12,878
you managed to get
your whole squad killed, Danny.

45
00:04:13,003 --> 00:04:14,921
-Bravo.
-Come on, man. Those things sting.

46
00:04:15,005 --> 00:04:16,882
What things?
These things? Ow!

47
00:04:16,965 --> 00:04:18,967
You know, I wouldn't know.
I haven't been hit yet.

48
00:04:19,134 --> 00:04:21,094
Ow! Okay, you know what?
That's too close, man.

49
00:04:21,219 --> 00:04:23,096
-[soldiers laughing]
-You could've taken out an eye.

50
00:04:23,221 --> 00:04:25,348
I got a date tonight, man.
This ain't sexy!

51
00:04:25,474 --> 00:04:27,476
-You're right. I'm sorry.
-Ow!

52
00:04:27,559 --> 00:04:29,060
-That one was on me.
-[yelping]

53
00:04:29,186 --> 00:04:30,562
That's a malfunctioning trigger.

54
00:04:30,729 --> 00:04:32,022
This weapon is just faulty.

55
00:04:32,147 --> 00:04:33,732
Someone is going to get
a talking to...

56
00:04:33,815 --> 00:04:34,941
Man, would you stop?

57
00:04:35,025 --> 00:04:36,818
All right, just stop.

58
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:40,447
[sighs] I should've
let you die in Grenada.

59
00:04:40,572 --> 00:04:42,431
If you did, we wouldn't be able
to come to the forest,

60
00:04:42,532 --> 00:04:43,825
run around and play
these awesome games.

61
00:04:43,909 --> 00:04:45,076
[Danny] Exactly.

62
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:46,411
[grunts]

63
00:04:46,578 --> 00:04:48,622
[muffled] Oh, I hate you.

64
00:04:48,789 --> 00:04:50,081
Wow, man, that hurts.

65
00:04:50,373 --> 00:04:51,416
'Cause I love you.

66
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,668
But you refuse to let it in
'cause you got intimacy issues.

67
00:04:53,794 --> 00:04:56,129
A therapist will probably tell you
you weren't hugged enough as a kid.

68
00:04:56,213 --> 00:04:58,715
-Look, man.
-Danny, I know I look stupid, but...

69
00:05:00,425 --> 00:05:02,719
-Hey, yo, take cover!
-[grunts]

70
00:05:04,179 --> 00:05:05,472
[all grunt]

71
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:09,476
[groans]

72
00:05:13,021 --> 00:05:14,064
[coughs]

73
00:05:14,189 --> 00:05:16,024
-[groans] Danny.
-[coughs]

74
00:05:16,525 --> 00:05:17,818
You okay?

75
00:05:18,109 --> 00:05:19,778
Uh, yeah, man. [grunts]

76
00:05:22,572 --> 00:05:24,241
This is Agent Jack Burns.

77
00:05:24,407 --> 00:05:25,992
I need medical up here now.

78
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:27,536
We have a projectile strike

79
00:05:27,619 --> 00:05:29,162
in the northwest corner
of the training course.

80
00:05:29,579 --> 00:05:31,081
Multiple injuries.

81
00:05:31,748 --> 00:05:35,877
And would someone please explain to me
why you dropped napalm on your own guys!

82
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:37,754
[soldier on radio] Negative.

83
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:39,798
There are no live army drills
in the northwest sector.

84
00:05:39,923 --> 00:05:41,591
What the hell hit us, then?

85
00:05:54,729 --> 00:05:56,064
[soldier 1]
Target on your right!

86
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:15,458
I need all of you to fan out
and track that thing down now!

87
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:19,629
Drive!

88
00:06:25,927 --> 00:06:26,803
There!

89
00:06:30,557 --> 00:06:31,558
What the hell?

90
00:06:32,225 --> 00:06:33,476
Take it down!

91
00:06:37,522 --> 00:06:39,608
Get down there now
and flush that thing out!

92
00:06:40,775 --> 00:06:42,235
[soldier 2] There it is!

93
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:46,114
[shots firing]

94
00:06:50,827 --> 00:06:52,704
[soldier 2 on radio]
Target has been located, sir.

95
00:06:54,247 --> 00:06:55,123
Light it up!

96
00:07:03,048 --> 00:07:04,090
[brakes screech]

97
00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:07,052
Damn it!

98
00:07:11,848 --> 00:07:12,974
[grunts]

99
00:07:18,229 --> 00:07:19,439
Oh, no.

100
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:32,035
It's going for the mine!

101
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:33,787
Cut it off!

102
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:38,875
[grunts]

103
00:07:47,759 --> 00:07:49,177
[breathes heavily]

104
00:07:49,344 --> 00:07:50,845
[soldier] Move, move!

105
00:07:51,137 --> 00:07:52,430
[soldiers speaking indistinctly]

106
00:07:52,514 --> 00:07:54,140
[visor beeping]

107
00:08:03,775 --> 00:08:04,901
[Bumblebee] Please.

108
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,528
This is a mistake.

109
00:08:08,321 --> 00:08:09,990
Stay cool. Hold your fire.

110
00:08:10,323 --> 00:08:12,117
I don't want to hurt anyone.

111
00:08:12,242 --> 00:08:13,868
[aircraft approaching]

112
00:08:20,083 --> 00:08:21,710
Who called in the Air Force?

113
00:08:25,505 --> 00:08:27,757
That's not the Air Force.

114
00:08:32,637 --> 00:08:33,638
Run.

115
00:08:36,474 --> 00:08:37,976
[soldiers screaming]

116
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:47,610
[grunts]

117
00:08:53,450 --> 00:08:55,243
[revving]

118
00:08:56,202 --> 00:08:57,203
[Bumblebee grunts]

119
00:08:57,287 --> 00:08:58,913
Did you think you could hide?

120
00:08:58,997 --> 00:09:00,248
[grunting]

121
00:09:08,715 --> 00:09:10,759
Now you'll die screaming.

122
00:09:10,925 --> 00:09:12,927
-Like your friends!
-[both grunting]

123
00:09:14,596 --> 00:09:15,680
[grunting]

124
00:09:19,517 --> 00:09:21,603
[Bumblebee groaning]

125
00:09:25,148 --> 00:09:27,358
[grunting]

126
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:32,572
[engine sputters]

127
00:09:48,296 --> 00:09:50,590
Tell me where your friends are hiding.

128
00:09:50,882 --> 00:09:52,342
I'll never talk.

129
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:54,135
Is that right?

130
00:09:56,304 --> 00:09:57,931
Then let's make it official.

131
00:09:58,014 --> 00:09:59,849
[gagging]

132
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:03,520
[visor beeping]

133
00:10:21,037 --> 00:10:23,331
[Blitzwing takes off, lands]

134
00:10:27,377 --> 00:10:28,878
B-127...

135
00:10:29,796 --> 00:10:32,132
as a member of the Autobot resistance,

136
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:34,676
you are a traitor to Cybertron

137
00:10:34,801 --> 00:10:36,719
and are hereby sentenced

138
00:10:37,178 --> 00:10:38,054
to death.

139
00:10:40,723 --> 00:10:42,308
-[rapid beeping]
-[gasps]

140
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:45,937
No!

141
00:10:47,105 --> 00:10:48,273
No!

142
00:11:10,003 --> 00:11:11,921
[groaning]

143
00:11:21,639 --> 00:11:23,433
[groaning]

144
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:35,737
[breathing heavily]

145
00:11:42,493 --> 00:11:44,579
[heavy footsteps thudding]

146
00:11:46,664 --> 00:11:48,791
[metal creaking]

147
00:11:51,294 --> 00:11:53,963
[electricity crackles, buzzes]

148
00:11:57,050 --> 00:11:58,468
[visor beeping]

149
00:12:05,850 --> 00:12:07,560
[children chattering indistinctly]

150
00:12:11,940 --> 00:12:13,358
[system powers down]

151
00:12:16,194 --> 00:12:18,738
-[alarm blaring]
-[Charlie groaning]

152
00:12:21,366 --> 00:12:22,492
[Charlie] Ugh.

153
00:12:23,326 --> 00:12:24,577
Shut up.

154
00:12:30,041 --> 00:12:32,043
[indie rock music playing on Walkman]

155
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:38,132
♪ Sweetness, sweetness I was only joking ♪

156
00:12:38,216 --> 00:12:41,678
♪ When I said by rights
You should be ♪

157
00:12:41,761 --> 00:12:45,056
♪ Bludgeoned in your bed ♪

158
00:12:46,557 --> 00:12:49,352
♪ And now I know
How Joan of Arc felt ♪

159
00:12:49,435 --> 00:12:53,356
♪ Now I know
How Joan of Arc felt ♪

160
00:12:54,565 --> 00:12:55,817
Morning, Dad.

161
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:57,860
♪ As the flames rose
To her Roman nose ♪

162
00:12:58,027 --> 00:13:01,322
♪ And her Walkman started to melt ♪

163
00:13:13,042 --> 00:13:15,420
[air drumming to drum roll on track]

164
00:13:22,218 --> 00:13:23,845
[sniffing]

165
00:13:26,681 --> 00:13:29,600
♪ Bigmouth, la-da-da da-da ♪

166
00:13:29,684 --> 00:13:32,353
♪ Bigmouth, la-da-da da-da ♪

167
00:13:32,437 --> 00:13:34,022
♪ Bigmouth... ♪

168
00:13:34,939 --> 00:13:37,150
[Sally] No! Don't tickle.

169
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:39,235
Ow! [laughing]

170
00:13:41,779 --> 00:13:42,822
Uh-oh!

171
00:13:43,448 --> 00:13:44,449
Caught.

172
00:13:45,116 --> 00:13:46,909
-Gross, Ron.
-[Sally laughing]

173
00:13:47,201 --> 00:13:48,286
Excuse me.

174
00:13:50,413 --> 00:13:52,623
Wha-- Are those your diving trophies?

175
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:54,375
Taking up too much space in my room.

176
00:13:54,459 --> 00:13:56,169
You're gonna regret doing that.

177
00:13:57,295 --> 00:13:58,629
Where's breakfast?

178
00:13:58,963 --> 00:14:02,425
Breakfast is conveniently
located in the cupboards and the fridge.

179
00:14:02,717 --> 00:14:04,010
-Ah.
-[Sally] Try to help out...

180
00:14:04,093 --> 00:14:05,511
-Yeah.
-...a little.

181
00:14:05,595 --> 00:14:08,890
Since I'm such a big kid now,
making my own breakfast and what have you.

182
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:12,018
You know how I could be
an even bigger help around here, Mom?

183
00:14:12,643 --> 00:14:13,770
If I had a car.

184
00:14:13,895 --> 00:14:14,854
Charlie.

185
00:14:15,021 --> 00:14:17,106
What do you know,
it's my birthday tomorrow,

186
00:14:17,273 --> 00:14:19,067
perfect timing for a large cash gift.

187
00:14:19,484 --> 00:14:21,944
You know, $500 is really all I need
to finish the Corvette.

188
00:14:22,028 --> 00:14:25,990
I don't have $500.
You know how much nurses make.

189
00:14:26,407 --> 00:14:29,035
"Half as much as doctors
for twice the work," right?

190
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:30,203
Tell you what, kiddo...

191
00:14:30,370 --> 00:14:31,704
I got another job interview tomorrow.

192
00:14:31,829 --> 00:14:33,956
If all goes well,
I'll have you swimming in car parts.

193
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:35,833
-[Conan whining]
-I prefer cash, Ron.

194
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:37,835
Don't be rude. Feed the dog.

195
00:14:38,211 --> 00:14:40,004
Conan is Otis's dog. Make him do it.

196
00:14:40,129 --> 00:14:41,506
[Otis] What?

197
00:14:41,589 --> 00:14:45,259
[Sally] Aw! You look so grown up
in your karate suit.

198
00:14:45,510 --> 00:14:47,887
My baby boy is becoming a man.

199
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:50,598
Oh, shoot, I'm gonna be late.

200
00:14:50,681 --> 00:14:54,185
Can you drop your brother at karate
on your way to work, please?

201
00:14:54,268 --> 00:14:56,229
Um, I could if I had a car.

202
00:14:56,312 --> 00:14:59,774
Just let him follow you on your bike
so nobody abducts him.

203
00:14:59,857 --> 00:15:01,401
Abducts him?

204
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:02,944
You just said he's a grown man now.

205
00:15:03,027 --> 00:15:06,364
If anyone tries anything,
I will rupture their freaking spleen.

206
00:15:07,532 --> 00:15:09,659
[riders screaming]

207
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:26,467
♪ And do you feel scared? I do ♪

208
00:15:26,551 --> 00:15:29,762
♪ But I won't stop and falter ♪

209
00:15:31,222 --> 00:15:32,723
♪ And if we threw it all away ♪

210
00:15:32,974 --> 00:15:33,975
[laughter]

211
00:15:35,643 --> 00:15:38,229
♪ Things can only get better... ♪

212
00:15:40,106 --> 00:15:41,941
-That's two for you guys.
-[man] Thanks, bro.

213
00:15:42,024 --> 00:15:44,026
All right. Have a good one.

214
00:15:44,318 --> 00:15:45,862
Eat safe. [chuckles]

215
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:53,202
[kids screaming]

216
00:15:53,286 --> 00:15:55,121
Excuse me. Hi.
We've never actually met...

217
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:56,539
Sorry, I can't right now.

218
00:15:56,622 --> 00:15:58,541
-Yeah. Oh, okay.
-[girls giggling]

219
00:15:59,876 --> 00:16:01,961
-[girl] Whoo!
-[boy] Hey, hot dog girl!

220
00:16:02,378 --> 00:16:03,838
-[Charlie] Oh, my God!
-[gasps]

221
00:16:03,921 --> 00:16:05,047
I'm so sorry.

222
00:16:05,506 --> 00:16:07,049
Oh, God.

223
00:16:07,592 --> 00:16:10,303
[in sing-song]
Someone's getting fired.

224
00:16:10,386 --> 00:16:13,389
If I had to wear that,
I would pray to be fired.

225
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:15,016
Good one, Tina.

226
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:19,479
Let's go.

227
00:16:21,522 --> 00:16:22,523
Oops.

228
00:16:22,607 --> 00:16:23,608
Ooh.

229
00:16:31,908 --> 00:16:33,493
♪ On the street where you live ♪

230
00:16:33,576 --> 00:16:36,454
♪ Girls talk
about their social lives ♪

231
00:16:37,497 --> 00:16:39,999
♪ They're made of lipstick
Plastic and paint ♪

232
00:16:40,166 --> 00:16:42,627
♪ A touch of sable
In their eyes ♪

233
00:16:44,212 --> 00:16:46,422
♪ All your life
All you asked ♪

234
00:16:46,506 --> 00:16:48,716
♪ When is your Daddy
Gonna talk to you ♪

235
00:16:50,468 --> 00:16:52,678
♪ But we're living
In another world ♪

236
00:16:52,762 --> 00:16:54,931
♪ Tryin' to get
Your message through... ♪

237
00:16:55,890 --> 00:16:57,517
[static warbles]

238
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:58,726
Come on.

239
00:16:58,935 --> 00:17:00,269
[Charlie] Hey, Uncle Hank.

240
00:17:00,353 --> 00:17:02,647
Are you still working
on that damn car?

241
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:05,274
You still working
on that damn personality?

242
00:17:06,609 --> 00:17:08,945
-What have you got for me?
-Whatever you want.

243
00:17:09,028 --> 00:17:11,614
Russians are gonna
blow us all to hell anyway.

244
00:17:11,697 --> 00:17:13,074
That's the spirit.

245
00:17:13,616 --> 00:17:14,909
[Bill] Hey, kid.

246
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:17,203
Hand me the three-eighths, would you?

247
00:17:17,286 --> 00:17:19,247
-You working on the carburetor?
-[Bill] Mmm-hmm.

248
00:17:22,917 --> 00:17:25,670
-You need the half-inch.
-[Bill] I said the three...

249
00:17:26,128 --> 00:17:27,255
Huh.

250
00:17:29,298 --> 00:17:31,050
-Thanks, kid.
-Yep.

251
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:42,019
♪ You saw me standing ♪

252
00:17:42,103 --> 00:17:48,276
♪ By the wall corner
Of a main street ♪

253
00:17:48,943 --> 00:17:50,528
♪ Take a chance ♪

254
00:17:50,611 --> 00:17:57,577
♪ Like all dreamers
Can't find another way ♪

255
00:17:57,660 --> 00:18:00,580
♪ You don't have to dream it all ♪

256
00:18:00,663 --> 00:18:03,499
♪ Just live a day... ♪

257
00:18:06,877 --> 00:18:07,962
[grunts]

258
00:18:31,736 --> 00:18:33,529
[bees buzzing]

259
00:19:05,936 --> 00:19:06,979
[engine starts]

260
00:19:07,063 --> 00:19:08,648
[radio warbling]

261
00:19:16,656 --> 00:19:18,991
[overlapping radio chatter]

262
00:19:24,830 --> 00:19:27,249
[Shatter] Where is Optimus Prime?

263
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:29,877
He survived the fall of Cybertron.

264
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:31,796
And no rebellion is truly dead

265
00:19:31,879 --> 00:19:33,589
until the leader is vanquished.

266
00:19:33,964 --> 00:19:36,384
So, where is he?

267
00:19:36,717 --> 00:19:38,094
My name is Cliffjumper,

268
00:19:38,177 --> 00:19:40,304
lieutenant in the Autobot resistance.

269
00:19:40,721 --> 00:19:42,973
-My safe return will be considered...
-[grunting]

270
00:19:43,057 --> 00:19:44,725
[in sing-song] Wrong answer.

271
00:19:44,892 --> 00:19:46,018
[groaning]

272
00:19:46,143 --> 00:19:48,437
[Shatter] We know he's planning
to establish a base.

273
00:19:48,562 --> 00:19:51,107
Tell us where it is
and we'll let you live.

274
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:54,151
My name is Cliffjumper,
lieutenant... [grunts]

275
00:19:54,235 --> 00:19:55,361
[music plays on radio]

276
00:19:55,444 --> 00:19:57,196
♪ Sometimes you wanna go... ♪

277
00:19:57,279 --> 00:19:58,531
[radio warbles]

278
00:19:58,614 --> 00:20:00,116
[Cliffjumper] No.

279
00:20:00,199 --> 00:20:02,368
[Shatter] That's B-127's signal.

280
00:20:02,451 --> 00:20:03,661
Can you trace it?

281
00:20:03,953 --> 00:20:05,371
Already did.

282
00:20:06,038 --> 00:20:10,501
If you won't tell us where Prime is,
perhaps your young friend will.

283
00:20:10,584 --> 00:20:11,627
Never.

284
00:20:11,794 --> 00:20:13,379
You're a brave warrior.

285
00:20:13,546 --> 00:20:15,798
You deserve a better death.

286
00:20:16,298 --> 00:20:18,175
[scoffs] But then again...

287
00:20:18,259 --> 00:20:19,552
[Dropkick grunts]

288
00:20:22,388 --> 00:20:24,014
[chuckles]

289
00:20:24,098 --> 00:20:26,434
Set course for Earth.

290
00:20:28,477 --> 00:20:29,895
[radio warbles, stops]

291
00:20:29,979 --> 00:20:31,605
[bees buzzing]

292
00:20:38,612 --> 00:20:40,072
I'll give you thirty bucks
for all of it.

293
00:20:40,281 --> 00:20:43,325
[chuckles] I can get twice that much
for the coil alone.

294
00:20:43,409 --> 00:20:45,369
From who? I'm the only one
that comes in here.

295
00:20:45,536 --> 00:20:47,037
I don't even know how you're still open.

296
00:20:47,121 --> 00:20:49,415
Just take it. Go. My show is on.

297
00:20:50,207 --> 00:20:51,792
[static crackling]

298
00:20:51,876 --> 00:20:53,627
Hey, where did you get that Beetle?

299
00:20:54,003 --> 00:20:57,381
I swear to God, ever since they put up
that dumbass tower,

300
00:20:57,465 --> 00:20:59,967
I can't get a signal to watch my shows.

301
00:21:00,134 --> 00:21:02,136
I've got to see what happens
to Alf this week.

302
00:21:13,272 --> 00:21:14,648
[Charlie] Come on!

303
00:21:14,732 --> 00:21:16,776
-[metal clattering]
-[Charlie sighs]

304
00:21:17,943 --> 00:21:19,195
[Charlie groans]

305
00:21:20,237 --> 00:21:22,031
[metal continues clattering]

306
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:28,204
[groans]

307
00:21:29,163 --> 00:21:30,581
Are you kidding me?

308
00:21:30,664 --> 00:21:32,458
[metal squeaking]

309
00:21:33,209 --> 00:21:34,543
[grunts in frustration]

310
00:21:35,461 --> 00:21:36,545
Damn it.

311
00:21:40,966 --> 00:21:42,468
[sighs]

312
00:21:42,551 --> 00:21:43,803
I give up.

313
00:21:46,055 --> 00:21:48,182
I can't do this without you.
[sobbing]

314
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:52,019
[Alf on TV] Nice to meet you.
Interested in a new Buick?

315
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:53,270
[all laugh]

316
00:21:53,354 --> 00:21:54,814
[Kate on TV] Nice try.

317
00:21:54,939 --> 00:21:56,607
[Alf] All right,
I touched. But I didn't eat.

318
00:21:56,690 --> 00:21:58,651
[Kate] And I'm supposed to believe
one of these steaks

319
00:21:58,734 --> 00:22:00,861
just got up and walked away on its own?

320
00:22:00,986 --> 00:22:02,655
[Alf] I've seen stranger.

321
00:22:03,280 --> 00:22:04,782
[Kate] No dinner for you tonight.

322
00:22:04,865 --> 00:22:06,325
[Alf] But I'm starved!

323
00:22:06,450 --> 00:22:08,786
I've been fasting since lunch!

324
00:22:08,911 --> 00:22:10,204
[laughter]

325
00:22:10,287 --> 00:22:12,581
[Alf] Well,
I did eat that pumpkin.

326
00:22:15,543 --> 00:22:17,169
[alarm blaring]

327
00:22:17,253 --> 00:22:18,712
[groans]

328
00:22:18,796 --> 00:22:20,381
[alarm continues blaring]

329
00:22:21,757 --> 00:22:22,842
[alarm stops]

330
00:22:33,018 --> 00:22:34,353
[softly] Happy birthday.

331
00:22:47,616 --> 00:22:48,868
I miss you, Dad.

332
00:22:50,619 --> 00:22:52,371
I think it's too low, honey.

333
00:22:52,454 --> 00:22:53,455
No.

334
00:22:53,539 --> 00:22:55,583
No, I think it goes to that button.

335
00:22:55,666 --> 00:22:56,667
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

336
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:59,378
I don't know about... Fix it.

337
00:22:59,461 --> 00:23:00,462
Hey.

338
00:23:00,546 --> 00:23:02,965
-Good morning, birthday girl!
-Hi.

339
00:23:03,048 --> 00:23:04,383
You look...

340
00:23:06,343 --> 00:23:07,344
nice.

341
00:23:08,470 --> 00:23:10,055
Happy birthday, baby.

342
00:23:10,472 --> 00:23:12,933
I love you. Come on, open your present.
I'm gonna be late for work.

343
00:23:14,685 --> 00:23:16,020
Thanks, Mom.

344
00:23:20,566 --> 00:23:22,234
Helmet. With...

345
00:23:22,902 --> 00:23:23,944
daffodils.

346
00:23:24,069 --> 00:23:27,781
So, I keep hearing
about people on mopeds

347
00:23:27,948 --> 00:23:29,909
getting run over
and their brains smashed in.

348
00:23:29,992 --> 00:23:31,619
You got to wear this from now on.

349
00:23:31,744 --> 00:23:34,705
I don't care if it's not the law.
It's our law.

350
00:23:34,872 --> 00:23:36,540
Plus, look how cute it is.

351
00:23:38,959 --> 00:23:39,877
Yeah.

352
00:23:40,044 --> 00:23:41,545
[Sally] Happy birthday.

353
00:23:42,171 --> 00:23:44,131
I actually got you
a little gift, too, Charlie.

354
00:23:44,214 --> 00:23:47,092
I mean, it's small,
but, it's from the heart.

355
00:23:53,557 --> 00:23:55,476
A smile is a powerful thing.

356
00:23:56,727 --> 00:23:58,103
It releases endorphins.

357
00:23:58,270 --> 00:23:59,438
It says to the world,

358
00:23:59,647 --> 00:24:01,315
"I'm fun and approachable."

359
00:24:03,859 --> 00:24:06,028
You know, there's a whole
chapter in here

360
00:24:06,153 --> 00:24:07,863
about how people who smile more often

361
00:24:07,947 --> 00:24:10,074
actually have more friends.

362
00:24:10,449 --> 00:24:11,992
That's unbelievable.

363
00:24:12,076 --> 00:24:13,744
I really think it's gonna
change your whole outlook

364
00:24:13,827 --> 00:24:15,537
if you smile more often.

365
00:24:32,471 --> 00:24:33,806
I want the Beetle.

366
00:24:35,182 --> 00:24:37,267
-What?
-The yellow Beetle, I want it.

367
00:24:37,351 --> 00:24:39,561
I'll make you a deal. If I get
that thing started, it's mine.

368
00:24:39,687 --> 00:24:41,063
That's no deal.

369
00:24:41,188 --> 00:24:42,606
That's just you taking my car.

370
00:24:42,773 --> 00:24:46,110
If I get it started, I keep it
and I work here every day for a year!

371
00:24:46,527 --> 00:24:48,487
I'll scrub the grease
off the floors, okay?

372
00:24:48,570 --> 00:24:51,490
I will pick up and organize
every scrap of paper in this place.

373
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:55,119
I'll even detail your horrible,
disgusting toilets.

374
00:24:57,454 --> 00:24:59,331
Please. It's my birthday.

375
00:25:00,207 --> 00:25:01,458
Sorry, no deal.

376
00:25:02,751 --> 00:25:04,211
'Cause we ain't hiring.

377
00:25:05,754 --> 00:25:06,922
It's yours, kid.

378
00:25:07,131 --> 00:25:08,173
Happy birthday.

379
00:25:10,050 --> 00:25:11,218
[gasps]

380
00:25:11,301 --> 00:25:12,177
Thank you.

381
00:25:14,513 --> 00:25:16,223
Thank you, thank you, thank you!

382
00:25:16,682 --> 00:25:18,600
And my toilets are gorgeous.

383
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:36,410
♪ Think about it
There must be higher love ♪

384
00:25:36,493 --> 00:25:41,415
♪ Down in the heart or hidden
In the stars above ♪

385
00:25:41,498 --> 00:25:45,252
♪ Without it
Life is a wasted time... ♪

386
00:25:48,380 --> 00:25:50,007
[Charlie] Oh, God, please.

387
00:25:51,133 --> 00:25:52,885
[engine stalling]

388
00:25:52,968 --> 00:25:54,344
Come on.

389
00:25:55,471 --> 00:25:56,972
[engine revs]

390
00:25:58,807 --> 00:25:59,892
Oh, my...

391
00:26:00,059 --> 00:26:01,602
Oh, my God!

392
00:26:02,394 --> 00:26:04,855
Oh, my God, thank you so much!
I love you!

393
00:26:06,315 --> 00:26:08,108
[car engine rumbling]

394
00:26:11,612 --> 00:26:13,614
That thing ain't even safe to drive.

395
00:26:13,822 --> 00:26:14,907
It's a deathtrap.

396
00:26:19,078 --> 00:26:20,412
She's happy, though.

397
00:26:20,496 --> 00:26:22,790
["Higher Love" playing]

398
00:26:22,915 --> 00:26:25,334
♪ Bring me a higher love ♪

399
00:26:27,252 --> 00:26:29,963
♪ Bring me a higher love ♪

400
00:26:32,466 --> 00:26:35,302
♪ Bring me a higher love ♪

401
00:26:36,637 --> 00:26:41,016
♪ Where's that higher love
I keep thinking of? ♪

402
00:26:41,767 --> 00:26:42,851
Man.

403
00:26:43,602 --> 00:26:44,895
Looks amazing.

404
00:26:57,241 --> 00:26:58,575
[whispers] What?

405
00:27:29,398 --> 00:27:30,524
[gasps]

406
00:27:42,911 --> 00:27:44,538
[gasping]

407
00:27:55,299 --> 00:27:56,800
[whispers]
Oh, my God.

408
00:27:56,884 --> 00:27:58,302
[gasping]

409
00:28:20,616 --> 00:28:22,242
[Sally] Charlie,
what was that noise?

410
00:28:22,390 --> 00:28:24,036
Nothing! I'm fine. Mom,
you should go back to bed.

411
00:28:24,244 --> 00:28:25,120
Everything's fine.

412
00:28:25,287 --> 00:28:27,497
-What the hell is that?
-Um, it's...

413
00:28:27,748 --> 00:28:30,459
What is that car doing in our garage?

414
00:28:30,542 --> 00:28:31,668
Car?

415
00:28:32,961 --> 00:28:35,380
Oh, that, uh, car...

416
00:28:36,590 --> 00:28:37,925
is my car.

417
00:28:38,508 --> 00:28:40,052
Uncle Hank gave it to me.

418
00:28:40,260 --> 00:28:42,221
-It runs.
-[softly] Yeah.

419
00:28:42,471 --> 00:28:43,680
Those aren't safe.

420
00:28:44,139 --> 00:28:46,642
I wish you would've told me
before you brought it home.

421
00:28:46,725 --> 00:28:48,185
Okay. Sorry.

422
00:28:49,144 --> 00:28:50,687
Um, I'm in the middle of some stuff, Mom.

423
00:28:50,812 --> 00:28:53,106
Okay, I'll get out of your hair, but...

424
00:28:54,066 --> 00:28:56,443
Tell me things sometime.

425
00:28:56,526 --> 00:28:58,028
-I'm your mother.
-Okay.

426
00:28:58,445 --> 00:28:59,529
Okay.

427
00:29:00,113 --> 00:29:01,240
Good night.

428
00:29:01,323 --> 00:29:04,076
-It really runs?
-Yeah, it really runs.

429
00:29:04,159 --> 00:29:05,160
[Sally] Cool.

430
00:29:16,338 --> 00:29:17,839
[Charlie] You still in there?

431
00:29:17,923 --> 00:29:19,007
[metal creaks]

432
00:29:21,593 --> 00:29:22,719
Okay.

433
00:29:23,011 --> 00:29:24,846
A little jumpy. I'm sorry.

434
00:29:35,357 --> 00:29:36,358
Okay.

435
00:29:39,486 --> 00:29:40,612
[grunts]

436
00:30:01,967 --> 00:30:02,968
Hi.

437
00:30:09,641 --> 00:30:11,018
[Bumblebee chirps]

438
00:30:15,897 --> 00:30:17,524
Oh, God, are you...

439
00:30:20,402 --> 00:30:21,903
Do you speak?

440
00:30:23,155 --> 00:30:24,489
[groans]

441
00:30:34,499 --> 00:30:35,834
I won't hurt you.

442
00:30:58,273 --> 00:30:59,483
[soft gasp]

443
00:31:01,526 --> 00:31:03,487
Can you understand me?

444
00:31:09,117 --> 00:31:10,327
What are you?

445
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:13,330
Where did you come from?

446
00:31:14,956 --> 00:31:16,500
Okay. It's okay.

447
00:31:16,583 --> 00:31:18,126
[breathing heavily]

448
00:31:25,675 --> 00:31:27,052
You like my shirt?

449
00:31:27,928 --> 00:31:29,221
You a metal fan?

450
00:31:30,013 --> 00:31:31,098
No, wait...

451
00:31:32,015 --> 00:31:33,683
Oh, who? Me?

452
00:31:34,768 --> 00:31:35,977
Who am I?

453
00:31:37,854 --> 00:31:38,980
Oh, I'm...

454
00:31:40,273 --> 00:31:41,483
Charlie.

455
00:31:42,776 --> 00:31:43,985
Charlie Watson.

456
00:31:44,277 --> 00:31:46,113
I'm 18.

457
00:31:46,780 --> 00:31:47,989
Today.

458
00:31:48,490 --> 00:31:50,200
Actually, it's my birthday today.

459
00:31:52,452 --> 00:31:53,620
What's your name?

460
00:31:57,249 --> 00:31:59,459
You don't know
or you don't have a name?

461
00:32:04,673 --> 00:32:06,299
You sound like a little bumblebee.

462
00:32:09,553 --> 00:32:11,555
I'm gonna call you that from now on.

463
00:32:14,474 --> 00:32:15,600
Bumblebee.

464
00:32:17,644 --> 00:32:19,062
Matches your outfit, too.

465
00:32:19,271 --> 00:32:21,189
-[Bumblebee hums]
-[chuckles softly]

466
00:32:35,495 --> 00:32:38,790
[country music playing]

467
00:32:38,915 --> 00:32:42,961
♪ All my exes live in Texas ♪

468
00:32:44,296 --> 00:32:46,047
[clattering]

469
00:32:46,173 --> 00:32:47,424
[Amber] I want a divorce, Roy!

470
00:32:47,549 --> 00:32:49,634
-Come on, Amber.
-Give me one good reason.

471
00:32:49,718 --> 00:32:51,887
You tried to sleep with my sister!

472
00:32:52,012 --> 00:32:53,263
Unsuccessfully!

473
00:32:53,472 --> 00:32:55,640
Yeah, you're unsuccessful at everything.

474
00:32:55,724 --> 00:32:58,435
That down payment was for a house.
You bought a car.

475
00:32:58,560 --> 00:33:01,897
How stupid are you, Roy?
We don't need a car. God!

476
00:33:01,980 --> 00:33:05,400
Now, just settle down for one second
and hear me out.

477
00:33:07,486 --> 00:33:09,654
-What the hell is that?
-What?

478
00:33:13,158 --> 00:33:15,827
Oh, God, Roy, that thing
is coming right for us!

479
00:33:15,911 --> 00:33:17,579
No, no, no, no, no...

480
00:33:17,662 --> 00:33:19,789
Not my car. Not my car.

481
00:33:19,873 --> 00:33:22,375
Please, God, no, not my car!

482
00:33:32,802 --> 00:33:34,304
Oh, thank God, my car.

483
00:33:35,680 --> 00:33:36,932
Yeah, I'm okay.

484
00:33:37,349 --> 00:33:38,642
Oh, that's good, baby.

485
00:33:39,059 --> 00:33:40,185
That's good.

486
00:33:41,353 --> 00:33:42,938
[both] Run. Run!

487
00:33:45,524 --> 00:33:46,983
[glass shattering]

488
00:33:54,950 --> 00:33:56,034
[Roy] Oh...

489
00:33:58,453 --> 00:34:00,830
-God!
-[engine revving]

490
00:34:02,582 --> 00:34:04,459
Is that my car?

491
00:34:06,670 --> 00:34:07,754
Hello...

492
00:34:22,227 --> 00:34:23,270
[Roy] Jeez!

493
00:34:23,353 --> 00:34:24,688
[Shatter] Earth.

494
00:34:24,771 --> 00:34:26,606
-[Amber] Roy!
-[Roy] Oh!

495
00:34:26,690 --> 00:34:28,441
How underwhelming.

496
00:34:28,525 --> 00:34:31,611
The indigenous life
is even more primitive than I expected.

497
00:34:33,363 --> 00:34:34,447
Hey...

498
00:34:34,531 --> 00:34:36,157
[screams]

499
00:34:36,449 --> 00:34:37,325
[gasping]

500
00:34:37,617 --> 00:34:39,828
Hmm. I like the way they pop.

501
00:34:40,036 --> 00:34:41,705
Focus, comrade.

502
00:34:42,038 --> 00:34:46,960
B-127's distress signal came
from the western coast of this continent.

503
00:34:47,168 --> 00:34:49,713
For now, we head west.

504
00:34:51,756 --> 00:34:53,216
[tires squealing]

505
00:34:57,053 --> 00:34:58,888
[alarm blaring]

506
00:35:04,227 --> 00:35:06,271
[Ron] When do they start
letting you use nunchucks?

507
00:35:06,354 --> 00:35:07,856
[Otis] I don't know, but I hope soon.

508
00:35:08,398 --> 00:35:11,067
-Morning! See you guys later.
-Where you off to so fast?

509
00:35:11,568 --> 00:35:13,528
Nowhere. Have a nice day.

510
00:35:15,697 --> 00:35:16,990
Morning, Bum--...

511
00:35:19,492 --> 00:35:20,619
Bee?

512
00:35:23,455 --> 00:35:24,831
Bee, where are you?

513
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:27,959
[breathing heavily]

514
00:35:28,043 --> 00:35:30,128
-Oh, God. Oh, God. Oh, God. Oh, God.
-[car door closes]

515
00:35:30,253 --> 00:35:31,254
-Bee!
-[engine starts]

516
00:35:31,338 --> 00:35:32,797
Where did you go?

517
00:35:38,678 --> 00:35:40,263
Otis!

518
00:35:40,555 --> 00:35:42,349
[panting] Have you seen my car?

519
00:35:42,432 --> 00:35:43,933
Unfortunately, yes.

520
00:35:44,142 --> 00:35:45,935
No, have you seen my car today?

521
00:35:46,061 --> 00:35:47,812
It was in the garage. Someone stole it!

522
00:35:47,937 --> 00:35:49,606
No, idiot. Mom took it.

523
00:35:49,773 --> 00:35:51,274
-[panting]
-She had to bring Conan to the vet

524
00:35:51,358 --> 00:35:53,318
because he swallowed, like,
a rubber glove or something

525
00:35:53,443 --> 00:35:54,903
and Ron needed the station wagon.

526
00:35:55,070 --> 00:35:56,363
Thank God.

527
00:35:59,032 --> 00:36:00,200
Wait.

528
00:36:01,618 --> 00:36:03,411
[continues panting]

529
00:36:05,955 --> 00:36:08,041
Hi. Excuse me. It's me again.

530
00:36:08,124 --> 00:36:10,126
-We never officially met, but...
-I can't right now. Sorry.

531
00:36:10,210 --> 00:36:11,586
Nope. Yep.

532
00:36:11,795 --> 00:36:13,296
[stutters] Okay.

533
00:36:13,421 --> 00:36:14,964
[whining]

534
00:36:16,966 --> 00:36:18,802
I know, buddy. Hang in there.

535
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:23,556
You can't eat everything you see.

536
00:36:23,723 --> 00:36:26,267
Just let this be
a good life lesson for you.

537
00:36:28,645 --> 00:36:31,481
Oh, my God. Stop it! Don't do that!

538
00:36:32,357 --> 00:36:33,316
[barking]

539
00:36:35,985 --> 00:36:37,529
Bee, no!

540
00:36:42,909 --> 00:36:44,327
-Mom?
-Whoa!

541
00:36:44,744 --> 00:36:47,080
Jesus! Charlie, what are you doing?

542
00:36:47,163 --> 00:36:48,748
Mom, you gotta pull over.

543
00:36:48,832 --> 00:36:51,543
-What the hell is going on?
-Just pull the car over.

544
00:36:51,626 --> 00:36:54,212
[Sally] Okay, okay. All right.

545
00:36:55,547 --> 00:36:56,798
[Conan whines]

546
00:36:57,173 --> 00:36:59,426
Would you put that robot junk away?

547
00:36:59,634 --> 00:37:01,052
What are you thinking?

548
00:37:01,136 --> 00:37:02,554
[Sally] You almost gave me a heart attack.

549
00:37:02,637 --> 00:37:05,932
I thought I was being carjacked.
I'm taking the dog to the vet.

550
00:37:06,015 --> 00:37:08,184
I can't believe you would take
him without me.

551
00:37:08,309 --> 00:37:09,769
Mom, I'm so worried about him!

552
00:37:09,936 --> 00:37:11,813
He's my dog, too, you know.

553
00:37:11,896 --> 00:37:14,232
What happened to Conan being Otis's dog?

554
00:37:14,315 --> 00:37:16,109
[sighs] Mom, you're
being hysterical, okay?

555
00:37:16,234 --> 00:37:18,236
You should not be driving
in such an emotional state.

556
00:37:18,319 --> 00:37:20,113
I know how you get during emergencies.

557
00:37:20,947 --> 00:37:22,115
I'm a nurse.

558
00:37:23,950 --> 00:37:25,285
Not of animals.

559
00:37:29,372 --> 00:37:33,084
Oh, okay. I'm happy for you to drive.

560
00:37:33,168 --> 00:37:35,253
You weren't wearing your helmet,
by the way.

561
00:37:35,336 --> 00:37:36,796
-I saw that.
-Oh, shoot.

562
00:37:39,841 --> 00:37:41,301
[whispers] Keep it together, Bee.

563
00:37:41,426 --> 00:37:43,052
[fax machine whirring]

564
00:37:48,975 --> 00:37:49,976
Sir?

565
00:37:51,227 --> 00:37:52,395
Sir.

566
00:37:52,479 --> 00:37:54,564
I thought you'd want
to see this immediately.

567
00:37:59,903 --> 00:38:01,613
-They sure?
-[Simmons] Yes, sir.

568
00:38:01,738 --> 00:38:03,573
Two of them just
made contact in Texas.

569
00:38:03,907 --> 00:38:05,867
Intel says they're heading west fast.

570
00:38:05,950 --> 00:38:07,452
Saddle up, Simmons.

571
00:38:08,495 --> 00:38:09,954
We're going to Texas.

572
00:38:11,998 --> 00:38:14,667
[Charlie] Okay, Bee,
we need to go over a few things.

573
00:38:16,503 --> 00:38:17,670
[sighs]

574
00:38:20,799 --> 00:38:22,383
Okay. We're all clear.

575
00:38:25,178 --> 00:38:28,014
All right. [spits]
I'm re-thinking the beach.

576
00:38:28,097 --> 00:38:29,098
Ugh.

577
00:38:30,642 --> 00:38:32,143
Oh, I'm good.

578
00:38:32,644 --> 00:38:34,145
No, I'm good, thanks.

579
00:38:36,481 --> 00:38:40,068
People can be terrible
about things they don't understand.

580
00:38:40,318 --> 00:38:42,862
If they find you, they'll probably
lock you up in a lab somewhere

581
00:38:42,946 --> 00:38:44,489
and cut you into tiny little pieces.

582
00:38:44,656 --> 00:38:47,367
It'll be... bad, trust me.

583
00:38:51,412 --> 00:38:54,916
The only person you can show
yourself around is me, okay?

584
00:38:57,043 --> 00:38:58,962
So, let's practice. You ready?

585
00:38:59,295 --> 00:39:01,089
If you see anyone besides me,
what do you do?

586
00:39:04,467 --> 00:39:06,636
Great. Perfect.
[chuckles] Come back now.

587
00:39:09,138 --> 00:39:11,641
Okay, so let's say we're driving
and all of a sudden...

588
00:39:11,808 --> 00:39:14,227
Oh, shoot! Somebody's here!
Hide, Bee, hide!

589
00:39:15,228 --> 00:39:17,021
[Bumblebee whirring]

590
00:39:26,739 --> 00:39:28,074
You serious?

591
00:39:32,287 --> 00:39:34,414
Bee, it's too late. You're already dead.

592
00:39:38,501 --> 00:39:39,752
It's all right.

593
00:39:40,003 --> 00:39:41,629
That's why we're practicing.

594
00:39:42,505 --> 00:39:43,840
You'll get it.

595
00:39:43,923 --> 00:39:47,427
[pilot] Fox-2 on approach.
Non-biologicals are inbound.

596
00:39:48,887 --> 00:39:50,889
[visor chiming]

597
00:39:56,603 --> 00:39:58,396
[indistinct radio chatter]

598
00:40:04,652 --> 00:40:08,114
The goal, sir, should be
to communicate with them.

599
00:40:08,323 --> 00:40:11,117
First contact with an alien species.

600
00:40:11,993 --> 00:40:14,704
I've spent my whole life
waiting for this moment.

601
00:40:14,787 --> 00:40:16,539
If they make one wrong move,

602
00:40:16,706 --> 00:40:17,790
we put 'em down.

603
00:40:33,222 --> 00:40:34,849
The humans are multiplying.

604
00:40:34,933 --> 00:40:36,476
Please let me kill them.

605
00:40:36,559 --> 00:40:37,644
Not yet.

606
00:40:37,727 --> 00:40:40,063
B-127's signal has gone silent.

607
00:40:41,230 --> 00:40:42,899
I have an idea.

608
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:46,027
Listen up! I'm Agent Burns

609
00:40:46,194 --> 00:40:47,654
and this is... Dr. Powell.

610
00:40:47,820 --> 00:40:51,282
We currently have 100 guns
pointed right at your head!

611
00:40:51,783 --> 00:40:53,284
So, state your business.

612
00:40:53,660 --> 00:40:55,411
[Shatter] People of Earth,

613
00:40:55,745 --> 00:40:59,499
we are Decepticon peacekeepers
patrolling the galaxy.

614
00:40:59,624 --> 00:41:01,042
[Dropkick] What are you doing?

615
00:41:01,793 --> 00:41:03,169
This is humiliating.

616
00:41:03,753 --> 00:41:06,839
We believe a dangerous criminal
from our world

617
00:41:06,923 --> 00:41:10,009
is hiding somewhere on yours.

618
00:41:10,093 --> 00:41:11,886
How is it you think we can help?

619
00:41:13,596 --> 00:41:15,598
We need your eyes.

620
00:41:16,432 --> 00:41:17,600
Wait.

621
00:41:18,017 --> 00:41:19,894
You want access to our satellites?

622
00:41:20,186 --> 00:41:22,689
[Shatter] Our scanners' range is limited.

623
00:41:22,772 --> 00:41:26,109
Your infrastructure is... primitive.

624
00:41:26,401 --> 00:41:29,654
But combined,
they could be quite powerful.

625
00:41:30,029 --> 00:41:31,489
No way! Out of the question!

626
00:41:31,572 --> 00:41:34,450
We have a common enemy, Agent Burns.

627
00:41:34,534 --> 00:41:36,869
There's a war raging on our planet.

628
00:41:36,953 --> 00:41:41,624
If B-127 isn't found,
that war may find its way here.

629
00:41:41,708 --> 00:41:43,084
Perhaps...

630
00:41:44,043 --> 00:41:46,004
We can find a way to help one another.

631
00:41:47,130 --> 00:41:49,048
We'll talk it over with our superiors.

632
00:41:49,173 --> 00:41:50,383
In the meantime,

633
00:41:50,550 --> 00:41:51,968
if you could follow us.

634
00:41:52,051 --> 00:41:54,429
Very well, friend Powell.

635
00:41:54,637 --> 00:41:56,431
Take us to your leader.

636
00:42:07,316 --> 00:42:09,986
[Charlie] Must suck being cooped up
in a VW all day, huh?

637
00:42:11,904 --> 00:42:13,865
Is there anyone that can help you?

638
00:42:14,073 --> 00:42:15,533
Do you have a family?

639
00:42:15,950 --> 00:42:18,661
You know, like a mom, dad, siblings?

640
00:42:18,745 --> 00:42:19,996
You all love each other?

641
00:42:22,665 --> 00:42:24,125
Or drive each other crazy

642
00:42:24,208 --> 00:42:26,753
and you can't wait to get away
and start a whole new life.

643
00:42:29,714 --> 00:42:31,674
[electricity crackles]

644
00:42:33,217 --> 00:42:34,927
Do you want me to see if I can fix it?

645
00:42:37,138 --> 00:42:38,681
I'll be gentle, I promise.

646
00:42:48,775 --> 00:42:49,942
[softly] Whoa.

647
00:42:50,026 --> 00:42:51,444
[electricity crackles]

648
00:42:53,613 --> 00:42:55,073
You lay down, okay?

649
00:42:58,743 --> 00:42:59,911
Hold still.

650
00:43:02,789 --> 00:43:04,499
I think maybe there's something...

651
00:43:16,552 --> 00:43:18,262
[Optimus distorted]
B-127,

652
00:43:18,888 --> 00:43:20,932
I pray this message finds you.

653
00:43:21,891 --> 00:43:24,977
-Our war rages on.
-[transmission breaking]

654
00:43:25,353 --> 00:43:26,687
...planet Earth...

655
00:43:27,897 --> 00:43:29,148
...survival...

656
00:43:42,912 --> 00:43:43,913
[grunts]

657
00:43:45,790 --> 00:43:47,125
[grunting]

658
00:43:54,340 --> 00:43:56,759
[Decepticon] Ravage, eject!

659
00:43:58,219 --> 00:43:59,804
[growling]

660
00:44:14,610 --> 00:44:16,195
[Optimus distorted]
...your mission...

661
00:44:16,654 --> 00:44:17,613
...soldier...

662
00:44:17,697 --> 00:44:18,781
I...

663
00:44:23,327 --> 00:44:24,579
Are you okay?

664
00:44:24,662 --> 00:44:25,830
[groans softly]

665
00:44:27,665 --> 00:44:28,791
Who was that?

666
00:44:29,584 --> 00:44:32,211
That voice said something
about a-- a war.

667
00:44:34,005 --> 00:44:35,131
Do you remember anything?

668
00:44:39,260 --> 00:44:43,347
Is the VW Beetle
some kind off... disguise?

669
00:44:44,307 --> 00:44:45,892
Are you hiding from something?

670
00:44:49,145 --> 00:44:50,354
Are you scared?

671
00:44:57,695 --> 00:45:00,031
[radio crackling and warbling]

672
00:45:03,117 --> 00:45:04,285
[Charlie] It's broken.

673
00:45:06,537 --> 00:45:07,580
It's okay.

674
00:45:08,247 --> 00:45:09,582
I think I can help.

675
00:45:10,082 --> 00:45:11,417
[Bumblebee chirps]

676
00:45:11,500 --> 00:45:12,585
Let's go home.

677
00:45:17,757 --> 00:45:19,675
[Allison on TV]
...and a basket case,

678
00:45:19,759 --> 00:45:20,941
[Claire] ...a princess...

679
00:45:21,041 --> 00:45:23,137
-[John] And a criminal.
-[Charlie] All right, I'm almost done.

680
00:45:23,221 --> 00:45:24,810
[Brian on TV]
Does that answer your question?

681
00:45:25,431 --> 00:45:26,432
[Charlie] No way.

682
00:45:26,515 --> 00:45:27,642
Are you actually watching it?

683
00:45:27,725 --> 00:45:29,477
♪ Don't you forget about me ♪

684
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:30,728
[chuckles]

685
00:45:30,811 --> 00:45:31,938
♪ Don't, don't, don't... ♪

686
00:45:32,021 --> 00:45:33,856
You can pop in another one
if you want.

687
00:45:43,616 --> 00:45:46,160
[Charlie's dad on tape]
Whoo! Come on, sweetie!

688
00:45:46,577 --> 00:45:48,329
You got this, Charlie girl!

689
00:45:52,375 --> 00:45:53,751
All right, Charlie girl!

690
00:45:53,834 --> 00:45:55,461
[crowd cheers and applauds]

691
00:45:55,544 --> 00:45:56,754
Hello, Brighton Falls.

692
00:45:56,879 --> 00:45:58,631
This is Charlie Watson,
future Olympic gold medalist.

693
00:45:58,714 --> 00:46:00,132
[laughs]
That was so perfect.

694
00:46:00,216 --> 00:46:02,134
-Thanks, Dad.
-[Charlie's dad] How do you feel?

695
00:46:02,218 --> 00:46:04,428
[Charlie] No, no,
why would you play this?

696
00:46:07,682 --> 00:46:09,350
Sorry. I just...

697
00:46:10,393 --> 00:46:11,519
I finished.

698
00:46:16,482 --> 00:46:18,067
Let's see if we got something.

699
00:46:18,985 --> 00:46:20,111
[Charlie clears throat]

700
00:46:21,237 --> 00:46:22,405
Okay.

701
00:46:31,914 --> 00:46:33,082
Okay.

702
00:46:34,000 --> 00:46:35,334
All right.

703
00:46:37,920 --> 00:46:39,505
[radio static]

704
00:46:39,588 --> 00:46:41,173
[synthpop music
playing on radio]

705
00:46:41,257 --> 00:46:43,259
Oh, my God, yes!

706
00:46:43,634 --> 00:46:44,760
It worked!

707
00:46:45,469 --> 00:46:47,221
Look at you go.

708
00:46:47,847 --> 00:46:49,682
You got some moves.

709
00:46:49,932 --> 00:46:51,600
[music continues playing]

710
00:46:54,729 --> 00:46:56,731
♪ Talking away ♪

711
00:46:56,814 --> 00:46:58,107
[Charlie] You know, Bee,

712
00:46:58,190 --> 00:47:00,067
music can help you
say what you're feeling.

713
00:47:00,443 --> 00:47:03,195
♪ I'll say it anyway ♪

714
00:47:04,155 --> 00:47:06,574
You're gonna love this.
It's brand new.

715
00:47:06,657 --> 00:47:08,367
♪ Shying away... ♪

716
00:47:08,451 --> 00:47:10,703
[indie rock music
playing on stereo]

717
00:47:13,164 --> 00:47:15,499
♪ Girlfriend in a coma, I know

718
00:47:15,583 --> 00:47:18,794
♪ I know, it's serious ♪

719
00:47:20,713 --> 00:47:22,006
Not a Smiths fan.

720
00:47:23,257 --> 00:47:24,550
Okay, um...

721
00:47:25,926 --> 00:47:27,011
Here.

722
00:47:27,845 --> 00:47:29,013
Try this.

723
00:47:29,138 --> 00:47:30,306
[dance-pop music
plays on stereo]

724
00:47:30,473 --> 00:47:32,308
♪ Never gonna give you up... ♪

725
00:47:33,392 --> 00:47:34,435
[clangs]

726
00:47:36,020 --> 00:47:37,229
Fine.

727
00:47:39,565 --> 00:47:41,400
Okay, where's my
Stevie Nicks?

728
00:47:44,362 --> 00:47:45,946
Joan Jett and the Blackhearts.

729
00:47:47,239 --> 00:47:48,699
Stones.

730
00:47:49,450 --> 00:47:51,827
Hey, hey, please don't touch those.
Please.

731
00:47:57,458 --> 00:47:58,834
They belonged to my dad.

732
00:48:15,309 --> 00:48:16,560
[chuckles softly]

733
00:48:18,354 --> 00:48:19,605
Do you want to hear it?

734
00:48:36,455 --> 00:48:39,083
[souls music playing on record player]

735
00:48:42,169 --> 00:48:44,755
We used to listen to this
while we'd work on the Corvette.

736
00:48:44,839 --> 00:48:49,510
♪ Oh, my love
My darling... ♪

737
00:48:50,136 --> 00:48:51,762
It was his favorite.

738
00:48:51,846 --> 00:48:55,891
♪ I've hungered for your touch
A long lonely time ♪

739
00:48:56,016 --> 00:48:58,144
He used to say
it would make the car feel better.

740
00:49:01,063 --> 00:49:02,481
[song continues playing]

741
00:49:02,565 --> 00:49:04,733
♪ Time...

742
00:49:05,192 --> 00:49:06,569
♪ Goes by so slowly ♪

743
00:49:06,652 --> 00:49:08,195
[sighs]

744
00:49:09,905 --> 00:49:12,450
We used to work on this car
every weekend together.

745
00:49:12,533 --> 00:49:15,703
♪ And time can do so much ♪

746
00:49:17,371 --> 00:49:18,789
It was our thing.

747
00:49:18,873 --> 00:49:21,375
♪ Are you still mine? ♪

748
00:49:21,459 --> 00:49:22,710
[sighs]

749
00:49:23,669 --> 00:49:24,962
That tape...

750
00:49:27,840 --> 00:49:29,300
[exhales]

751
00:49:29,383 --> 00:49:31,218
That was the last time
I saw him.

752
00:49:35,514 --> 00:49:37,016
He died of a heart attack.

753
00:49:39,727 --> 00:49:41,395
I never got
to say goodbye.

754
00:49:45,232 --> 00:49:47,485
You know,
I always thought if I could just...

755
00:49:48,819 --> 00:49:50,821
finish fixing this car...

756
00:49:54,825 --> 00:49:57,411
If I could just get it to start up again,

757
00:49:59,747 --> 00:50:01,123
he would hear me.

758
00:50:03,626 --> 00:50:04,960
He would hear me.

759
00:50:07,546 --> 00:50:09,632
[sighs heavily]

760
00:50:21,227 --> 00:50:22,311
[sniffling]

761
00:50:43,791 --> 00:50:45,376
I say this with all due respect.

762
00:50:46,043 --> 00:50:47,461
Have you lost your damn mind?

763
00:50:47,628 --> 00:50:48,810
That was with all due respect?

764
00:50:48,910 --> 00:50:50,548
[General Whalen] The man's
got a point, Doctor.

765
00:50:50,673 --> 00:50:51,966
Our satellite network

766
00:50:52,091 --> 00:50:54,093
is at the forefront
of our national defense.

767
00:50:54,176 --> 00:50:55,135
[Powell] Sir, please.

768
00:50:55,219 --> 00:50:57,930
It could be a once
in a lifetime opportunity.

769
00:50:58,013 --> 00:50:59,682
Can you imagine the advances

770
00:50:59,765 --> 00:51:01,600
an alliance with these
creatures might bring?

771
00:51:01,684 --> 00:51:02,935
[Agent Burns] I imagine the advances.

772
00:51:03,102 --> 00:51:04,728
An advance on Washington.

773
00:51:05,229 --> 00:51:07,898
-New York. An advance on Chicago!
-That's not gonna happen.

774
00:51:08,023 --> 00:51:10,526
They literally call themselves
"Decepticons."

775
00:51:10,943 --> 00:51:12,319
That doesn't set off
any red flags?

776
00:51:12,444 --> 00:51:14,738
Enough! From both of you.

777
00:51:14,822 --> 00:51:15,906
[Dr. Powell] Sir,

778
00:51:16,115 --> 00:51:20,452
we're talking about the most advanced
robotic system ever seen.

779
00:51:21,120 --> 00:51:22,621
If we tell them no,

780
00:51:23,122 --> 00:51:26,125
they'll just take their technology
to the Russians instead.

781
00:51:26,208 --> 00:51:28,168
[all murmuring]

782
00:51:28,294 --> 00:51:31,463
Do you really want to go down in history
as the man who cost us the Cold War?

783
00:51:31,547 --> 00:51:32,840
[sighs]

784
00:51:34,008 --> 00:51:35,050
Fine.

785
00:51:36,176 --> 00:51:38,554
We'll help them
find their fugitive.

786
00:51:39,221 --> 00:51:40,848
And when it's done,

787
00:51:41,181 --> 00:51:43,058
you can do all the experiments
you want. Hmm?

788
00:51:46,145 --> 00:51:47,146
Yes, sir.

789
00:51:48,480 --> 00:51:51,692
[Dr. Powell]
Gentle... uh, robots.

790
00:51:53,777 --> 00:51:55,654
Welcome to Sector 7.

791
00:51:55,946 --> 00:51:58,866
[Dropkick] How kind of you
to finally allow us in.

792
00:51:59,074 --> 00:52:01,577
We're very happy
to have you here as friends.

793
00:52:01,660 --> 00:52:03,621
Thank you, friend Powell.

794
00:52:03,704 --> 00:52:07,750
My superior has agreed to grant you
limited access to our satellites.

795
00:52:08,167 --> 00:52:10,753
In addition, you're welcome to use

796
00:52:11,086 --> 00:52:13,297
all of our technology here.

797
00:52:13,464 --> 00:52:16,091
It's the largest super-array
