-♪ I can't drive 55!
-[screaming]

1050
01:04:21,149 --> 01:04:22,609
[Charlie] Oh, my God!

1051
01:04:22,817 --> 01:04:24,903
[exclaiming]

1052
01:04:24,986 --> 01:04:29,324
-♪ I can't drive 55! ♪
-[both whimpering]

1053
01:04:29,824 --> 01:04:31,201
[sirens wailing]

1054
01:04:33,620 --> 01:04:35,455
Oh, my God, we're committing a felony!

1055
01:04:39,084 --> 01:04:40,251
[both gasp]

1056
01:04:40,335 --> 01:04:41,669
[breathing heavily]

1057
01:04:42,087 --> 01:04:43,713
We got a yellow vehicle

1058
01:04:43,797 --> 01:04:46,216
driving its damn self
through the Pico Tunnel.

1059
01:04:47,425 --> 01:04:49,386
[Charlie and Memo screaming]

1060
01:04:53,932 --> 01:04:55,308
[whimpering]

1061
01:04:56,601 --> 01:04:57,977
Uh...

1062
01:05:08,363 --> 01:05:09,489
[tires screech]

1063
01:05:11,116 --> 01:05:12,283
[both grunt]

1064
01:05:13,910 --> 01:05:14,953
[exhales]

1065
01:05:17,205 --> 01:05:19,207
[both laughing]

1066
01:05:29,634 --> 01:05:30,635
Good night.

1067
01:05:34,931 --> 01:05:35,974
Good-- Good night.

1068
01:05:44,107 --> 01:05:45,442
[sighs]

1069
01:05:45,817 --> 01:05:47,152
[whispers] Good night, Bee.

1070
01:06:00,707 --> 01:06:03,251
Morning, buddy. I got to go to work, okay?

1071
01:06:04,502 --> 01:06:07,672
Bee. Listen to me.
You need to stay in this garage, okay?

1072
01:06:07,755 --> 01:06:08,965
After what happened last night,

1073
01:06:09,048 --> 01:06:11,176
I'm pretty sure the cops
are looking for you,

1074
01:06:11,259 --> 01:06:13,678
and, uh, you don't exactly blend in.

1075
01:06:15,138 --> 01:06:16,431
I'll be back, all right?

1076
01:06:16,514 --> 01:06:17,849
[Bumblebee whines]

1077
01:06:20,143 --> 01:06:21,227
Here.

1078
01:06:23,480 --> 01:06:24,856
You can have my Pop-Tart.

1079
01:06:26,107 --> 01:06:28,026
[people screaming]

1080
01:06:30,612 --> 01:06:32,989
♪ Take your baby by the hand ♪

1081
01:06:34,491 --> 01:06:36,159
[sizzling]

1082
01:06:36,242 --> 01:06:38,828
I need you to go
to the frozen banana stand

1083
01:06:38,995 --> 01:06:40,455
and steal some sticks.

1084
01:06:41,623 --> 01:06:42,916
We're out of sticks.

1085
01:06:42,999 --> 01:06:45,543
Can't we just sell the
hot dogs without the sticks?

1086
01:06:46,002 --> 01:06:46,961
No.

1087
01:06:47,086 --> 01:06:48,379
[music playing on TV]

1088
01:06:48,463 --> 01:06:49,797
♪ Don't, don't, don't... ♪

1089
01:06:49,881 --> 01:06:51,633
[Bumblebee grunting]

1090
01:06:51,758 --> 01:06:53,384
[Conan whining]

1091
01:06:59,140 --> 01:07:00,767
[whimpers]

1092
01:07:24,541 --> 01:07:26,000
[bird chirping]

1093
01:07:57,448 --> 01:07:59,409
[gas fizzing]

1094
01:08:03,871 --> 01:08:05,081
[clattering]

1095
01:08:15,049 --> 01:08:16,134
[Conan barks]

1096
01:08:21,055 --> 01:08:22,348
[sofa creaks]

1097
01:08:30,440 --> 01:08:32,233
[clock ticking]

1098
01:08:47,498 --> 01:08:48,625
[dings]

1099
01:08:49,792 --> 01:08:51,210
[machine gurgling]

1100
01:09:10,647 --> 01:09:12,106
[powering up]

1101
01:09:22,200 --> 01:09:23,201
[beeping]

1102
01:09:26,454 --> 01:09:27,580
What's happening here?

1103
01:09:27,664 --> 01:09:29,582
We got a hit, I think.
Where's that location?

1104
01:09:29,666 --> 01:09:32,627
Near San Francisco.
A coastal town named Brighton Falls.

1105
01:09:43,971 --> 01:09:45,807
-[explosion]
-[dog barking]

1106
01:09:48,184 --> 01:09:49,644
[explosion]

1107
01:09:51,604 --> 01:09:53,523
You have a personal call.

1108
01:09:58,152 --> 01:10:00,697
-Hello?
-Charlie, hey, it's Memo.

1109
01:10:00,780 --> 01:10:02,699
You got to come home right now.

1110
01:10:05,410 --> 01:10:06,744
[engine revving]

1111
01:10:06,828 --> 01:10:08,204
[tires screech]

1112
01:10:09,997 --> 01:10:12,291
It's bad. It's really, really bad.

1113
01:10:15,086 --> 01:10:16,421
[Charlie gasps]

1114
01:10:17,755 --> 01:10:19,048
Where's Bumblebee?

1115
01:10:25,054 --> 01:10:28,349
Bumblebee, what have you done?

1116
01:10:28,433 --> 01:10:30,476
What were you thinking? What...

1117
01:10:31,227 --> 01:10:33,396
I told you to hide in the garage!

1118
01:10:35,398 --> 01:10:36,566
Great.

1119
01:10:36,941 --> 01:10:38,609
Helpful shame spiral, Bee.

1120
01:10:38,860 --> 01:10:40,486
[Bumblebee whines]

1121
01:10:40,737 --> 01:10:42,113
I'm not mad, okay?

1122
01:10:42,196 --> 01:10:43,990
This is all my fault.

1123
01:10:44,449 --> 01:10:45,950
I never should have left you.

1124
01:10:50,705 --> 01:10:52,790
[Memo] Hey, okay, maybe don't
transform all the way?

1125
01:10:52,874 --> 01:10:55,042
We've still got
to get you through the door.

1126
01:10:55,126 --> 01:10:56,335
[Bumblebee groans]

1127
01:10:56,419 --> 01:10:57,670
Come on, buddy.

1128
01:10:58,755 --> 01:10:59,922
It's okay.

1129
01:11:09,265 --> 01:11:10,683
-[sighs]
-[objects clattering]

1130
01:11:14,103 --> 01:11:16,022
[breathing heavily]

1131
01:11:19,192 --> 01:11:20,610
I am so screwed.

1132
01:11:31,078 --> 01:11:32,663
[grunting]

1133
01:11:34,332 --> 01:11:36,751
And now you're crippled for life.

1134
01:11:36,834 --> 01:11:38,628
Honey, watch the hair.

1135
01:11:40,588 --> 01:11:42,048
-[door closes]
-[indistinct chatter]

1136
01:11:44,342 --> 01:11:47,178
Go. Now. But be quiet.

1137
01:11:47,261 --> 01:11:48,554
Mom, wait!

1138
01:11:48,763 --> 01:11:49,847
[gasps]

1139
01:11:50,932 --> 01:11:52,225
Oh, my God!

1140
01:11:54,018 --> 01:11:54,977
[gasps]

1141
01:11:55,144 --> 01:11:56,604
-Mom...
-[Sally] What happened?

1142
01:11:56,979 --> 01:11:58,940
[Charlie] I'm sorry. This is all my fault.

1143
01:11:59,023 --> 01:12:00,525
What'd you do to my TV?

1144
01:12:00,733 --> 01:12:02,401
Look, Mom, I can explain.

1145
01:12:02,485 --> 01:12:04,237
We will talk about this later, all right?

1146
01:12:04,320 --> 01:12:06,072
-Now, I have to go.
-Are you kidding me?

1147
01:12:06,447 --> 01:12:07,657
No. You're not going anywhere.

1148
01:12:07,949 --> 01:12:09,742
It's about my car. It's really important.

1149
01:12:09,909 --> 01:12:11,118
About your car?

1150
01:12:11,285 --> 01:12:13,496
That you spend all day
and night shut in that garage,

1151
01:12:13,579 --> 01:12:14,997
doing God-knows-what with?

1152
01:12:15,081 --> 01:12:17,124
Mom, I can't. I really can't right now.

1153
01:12:17,208 --> 01:12:19,418
Oh, no, you really can, Charlie.

1154
01:12:19,710 --> 01:12:21,462
You really can.

1155
01:12:21,546 --> 01:12:22,547
I have had it!

1156
01:12:22,797 --> 01:12:25,383
Your attitude, your always sulking around.

1157
01:12:25,633 --> 01:12:28,928
You brought home that piece of crap
without even asking me!

1158
01:12:29,011 --> 01:12:32,056
Everyone in this family
is trying to be happy,

1159
01:12:32,223 --> 01:12:34,392
and all you want to do
is make things harder.

1160
01:12:34,559 --> 01:12:36,477
You know, Mom,
just because you've moved on

1161
01:12:36,561 --> 01:12:39,272
and you're happy with your
new life doesn't mean I have!

1162
01:12:40,022 --> 01:12:42,650
You've found a replacement
for my dad and I haven't,

1163
01:12:42,733 --> 01:12:43,943
okay, and I never will!

1164
01:12:44,068 --> 01:12:46,070
So, I'm sorry if that makes things harder,

1165
01:12:46,237 --> 01:12:47,989
but in ten months from now

1166
01:12:48,072 --> 01:12:49,657
you won't even have to deal with me!

1167
01:12:51,617 --> 01:12:52,827
Charlie!

1168
01:12:54,495 --> 01:12:55,580
[sighs]

1169
01:13:02,879 --> 01:13:04,130
Hey, you okay?

1170
01:13:06,007 --> 01:13:07,133
Yeah.

1171
01:13:10,177 --> 01:13:12,179
I just feel like ever since my dad died,

1172
01:13:12,263 --> 01:13:15,016
I've become this drain on everyone,
and I hate it.

1173
01:13:16,851 --> 01:13:19,812
It's like everybody expects me
to act like nothing ever happened, and...

1174
01:13:20,479 --> 01:13:22,064
it's impossible to do that.

1175
01:13:25,067 --> 01:13:26,444
About your dad...

1176
01:13:26,819 --> 01:13:27,904
I'm really sorry.

1177
01:13:28,529 --> 01:13:29,614
Thanks.

1178
01:13:30,531 --> 01:13:31,699
You know, there's...

1179
01:13:31,949 --> 01:13:33,200
there's this quote that I like.

1180
01:13:35,077 --> 01:13:38,289
"The darkest nights
produce the brightest stars."

1181
01:13:42,710 --> 01:13:44,003
That's nice.

1182
01:13:45,171 --> 01:13:46,797
My mom got it from Weight Watchers.

1183
01:13:49,133 --> 01:13:50,343
[chuckles softly]

1184
01:13:53,638 --> 01:13:54,639
[brakes squeal]

1185
01:14:01,812 --> 01:14:04,357
Get out and move away from the vehicle.

1186
01:14:04,440 --> 01:14:05,524
[engine revs]

1187
01:14:05,650 --> 01:14:07,360
Stay cool, Bee.

1188
01:14:07,443 --> 01:14:09,445
[revs and stops]

1189
01:14:16,577 --> 01:14:17,578
What's going on?

1190
01:14:17,662 --> 01:14:18,955
[Memo grunts]

1191
01:14:19,038 --> 01:14:20,039
Hey!

1192
01:14:20,122 --> 01:14:21,624
-Come on!
-[Charlie] Stop it!

1193
01:14:22,458 --> 01:14:23,918
Let go of me!

1194
01:14:24,168 --> 01:14:25,044
[screams]

1195
01:14:25,127 --> 01:14:27,129
-Weapons now! Take it down!
-Run!

1196
01:14:27,338 --> 01:14:29,048
No, don't run. Do not run!

1197
01:14:29,173 --> 01:14:30,424
[Charlie grunts]

1198
01:14:33,010 --> 01:14:33,970
She ran.

1199
01:14:34,261 --> 01:14:35,721
[Charlie screaming]

1200
01:14:40,935 --> 01:14:42,103
[grunts]

1201
01:14:44,355 --> 01:14:46,607
[helicopter blades whirring]

1202
01:14:46,691 --> 01:14:48,526
-[engine revs]
-[tires screech]

1203
01:14:57,743 --> 01:14:59,203
Please tell me they're on our side.

1204
01:15:05,376 --> 01:15:06,711
[grunts]

1205
01:15:06,794 --> 01:15:08,129
[groans]

1206
01:15:12,258 --> 01:15:13,843
[Shatter] No more running.

1207
01:15:14,260 --> 01:15:15,970
No more hiding.

1208
01:15:16,387 --> 01:15:18,139
[visor trilling]

1209
01:15:20,057 --> 01:15:24,645
B-127, you're a traitor and a coward.

1210
01:15:24,895 --> 01:15:26,981
Tell us where Optimus Prime is hiding.

1211
01:15:30,276 --> 01:15:32,069
-Bee, look out!
-[Dropkick grunts]

1212
01:15:33,988 --> 01:15:35,906
[Dropkick] Why isn't he fighting back?

1213
01:15:35,990 --> 01:15:37,992
-[Charlie grunts]
-[Dropkick] Why don't you fight?

1214
01:15:38,242 --> 01:15:39,285
Leave him alone! Please!

1215
01:15:43,497 --> 01:15:44,790
Again.

1216
01:15:44,874 --> 01:15:46,709
[electricity crackling]

1217
01:15:48,085 --> 01:15:48,961
Hit it again!

1218
01:15:50,921 --> 01:15:52,131
Stop! Stop it!

1219
01:15:52,214 --> 01:15:54,091
[grunts and groans]

1220
01:16:07,354 --> 01:16:09,732
[breathing steadily]

1221
01:16:09,815 --> 01:16:11,942
[muffled conversations]

1222
01:16:14,236 --> 01:16:15,571
[groans]

1223
01:16:22,995 --> 01:16:25,623
[Agent Burns] Your daughter
stole government property, Mrs. Watson.

1224
01:16:25,706 --> 01:16:27,958
[Sally] She's been
having trouble adjusting,

1225
01:16:28,084 --> 01:16:30,628
but we had no idea it was this serious.

1226
01:16:30,711 --> 01:16:31,921
I...

1227
01:16:32,004 --> 01:16:33,380
Charlie. Honey.

1228
01:16:33,464 --> 01:16:36,092
I didn't steal anything,
and he doesn't belong to them.

1229
01:16:36,467 --> 01:16:38,135
-"He?"
-[Agent Burns] Ma'am.

1230
01:16:38,219 --> 01:16:40,346
I can assure you that it is an "it".

1231
01:16:40,596 --> 01:16:42,598
And "it" is a highly dangerous
war machine.

1232
01:16:42,807 --> 01:16:44,100
No, he isn't, okay, Mom?

1233
01:16:44,225 --> 01:16:45,851
He's not some "war machine."

1234
01:16:45,935 --> 01:16:48,687
I-- I don't know what he is, but...

1235
01:16:49,188 --> 01:16:50,397
He's my friend.

1236
01:16:51,107 --> 01:16:53,484
Ma'am, your daughter's had
a traumatic experience today.

1237
01:16:53,818 --> 01:16:55,986
Maybe doesn't understand
everything she's seen.

1238
01:16:56,112 --> 01:16:57,363
She's disoriented.

1239
01:16:57,446 --> 01:16:59,949
No, I'm fine, Mom.
I'm completely fine, okay?

1240
01:17:00,032 --> 01:17:02,743
You have to believe me, please.
I didn't steal anything!

1241
01:17:02,868 --> 01:17:05,037
Stop! Just go to your room.

1242
01:17:05,788 --> 01:17:07,206
[sighs]

1243
01:17:12,378 --> 01:17:14,797
When I was going through puberty,

1244
01:17:15,422 --> 01:17:17,091
I stole things, too.

1245
01:17:17,925 --> 01:17:20,386
-Stole a box of Mallomars once.
-Yeah, we know.

1246
01:17:22,429 --> 01:17:23,848
[sighs]

1247
01:17:59,550 --> 01:18:00,968
[mouthing]

1248
01:18:04,054 --> 01:18:05,055
[Otis] Boom.

1249
01:18:06,140 --> 01:18:07,433
Caught you.

1250
01:18:07,892 --> 01:18:09,727
Oh, Mom's gonna love this.

1251
01:18:09,810 --> 01:18:11,437
Look, Otis, you need to go home and...

1252
01:18:11,520 --> 01:18:13,063
Mom!

1253
01:18:13,147 --> 01:18:14,646
No, Otis, stop it!

1254
01:18:14,796 --> 01:18:15,941
-Why would you do that?
-[grunting]

1255
01:18:16,025 --> 01:18:17,193
Let go of me!

1256
01:18:17,276 --> 01:18:18,819
-You're touching my buttocks!
-[shushes]

1257
01:18:19,153 --> 01:18:21,488
I will tell you a secret if you shut up.

1258
01:18:22,740 --> 01:18:26,493
Okay, so, um, this is my room.

1259
01:18:26,577 --> 01:18:28,329
Just make yourself at home.

1260
01:18:28,495 --> 01:18:30,456
These are actually my sister's stuff.

1261
01:18:30,539 --> 01:18:33,417
She likes playing pranks,
like putting her stuff over here.

1262
01:18:33,500 --> 01:18:35,669
-[Charlie] Can I, uh, sit down?
-Yeah, yeah. Mmm-hmm.

1263
01:18:35,753 --> 01:18:37,254
[reporter on TV]
Residents of Brighton Falls

1264
01:18:37,338 --> 01:18:39,757
have been witness
to an unusual sight this evening.

1265
01:18:39,840 --> 01:18:43,302
Armed Forces pouring into town
as part of what we are told

1266
01:18:43,385 --> 01:18:46,013
is a routine military exercise

1267
01:18:46,096 --> 01:18:48,849
setting up camp
at our own McKinnon Air Base.

1268
01:18:49,016 --> 01:18:51,352
If Bumblebee's still alive,
that's where they're keeping him.

1269
01:18:52,311 --> 01:18:54,146
We have to go.
We have to try and save him.

1270
01:18:54,230 --> 01:18:56,023
Count me in. I'll take point.

1271
01:18:57,107 --> 01:18:58,609
-No, you won't.
-Come on.

1272
01:18:58,692 --> 01:18:59,944
No, Otis.

1273
01:19:00,069 --> 01:19:02,321
-But I can help. Master Larry says I--
-I need someone here.

1274
01:19:02,738 --> 01:19:04,156
I need someone reliable

1275
01:19:04,281 --> 01:19:06,200
to make sure that Mom and Ron
don't know that I'm gone.

1276
01:19:06,951 --> 01:19:08,077
I'm someone reliable.

1277
01:19:10,079 --> 01:19:11,205
Hell, yeah, you are.

1278
01:19:16,168 --> 01:19:17,169
Good luck.

1279
01:19:18,087 --> 01:19:19,296
You, too.

1280
01:19:19,588 --> 01:19:20,673
Get over here.

1281
01:19:21,590 --> 01:19:22,800
[Charlie sighing]

1282
01:19:25,970 --> 01:19:27,096
Oh.

1283
01:19:27,179 --> 01:19:28,389
Let's do this.

1284
01:19:31,100 --> 01:19:34,270
[Shatter] Tell us where
Optimus Prime and the rebels are hiding,

1285
01:19:34,561 --> 01:19:36,897
and we can end this war.

1286
01:19:39,191 --> 01:19:40,192
Talk!

1287
01:19:40,276 --> 01:19:42,486
[Dr. Powell] Who is Optimus Prime?

1288
01:19:42,569 --> 01:19:44,822
[Shatter] This doesn't
concern you, human Powell.

1289
01:19:45,281 --> 01:19:47,408
Last chance.

1290
01:19:47,908 --> 01:19:48,826
[metal clangs]

1291
01:19:53,872 --> 01:19:55,708
[Memo] Are you sure this is a good idea?

1292
01:19:56,625 --> 01:19:58,669
[Charlie] It's a terrible idea,
but I've got to try it.

1293
01:19:58,794 --> 01:20:01,297
[Memo] You can't get--
Well, why don't you-- Stop, stop, wait...

1294
01:20:01,380 --> 01:20:04,258
-How'd you know the power was off?
-[Charlie] I didn't. Let's go.

1295
01:20:09,972 --> 01:20:11,223
[Dropkick] Can I?

1296
01:20:11,307 --> 01:20:13,392
[Shatter] His Memory cells are fried.

1297
01:20:14,226 --> 01:20:15,477
Finish him.

1298
01:20:15,561 --> 01:20:16,854
[Dropkick grunts]

1299
01:20:22,151 --> 01:20:23,610
[Optimus] We will fight on.

1300
01:20:23,902 --> 01:20:27,197
Regroup, rebuild, and retake our home.

1301
01:20:27,448 --> 01:20:29,533
But we must find refuge first.

1302
01:20:29,616 --> 01:20:30,993
You will travel to Earth.

1303
01:20:31,368 --> 01:20:34,121
Once we've gathered the others,
we'll join you.

1304
01:20:34,413 --> 01:20:36,540
You must protect the planet.

1305
01:20:36,707 --> 01:20:38,709
If the Decepticons find it,

1306
01:20:38,834 --> 01:20:41,628
then our people are truly finished.

1307
01:20:42,004 --> 01:20:43,797
Stay safe, soldier.

1308
01:20:44,214 --> 01:20:46,300
I am coming.

1309
01:20:48,135 --> 01:20:50,429
Prime is coming here?

1310
01:20:50,679 --> 01:20:52,765
They're all coming here.

1311
01:20:53,265 --> 01:20:57,269
This is our chance to wipe out the Autobot
resistance for good.

1312
01:20:57,478 --> 01:21:00,314
We'll burn the whole planet to cinders.

1313
01:21:01,106 --> 01:21:03,192
[Shatter] We must get word
to Cybertron immediately.

1314
01:21:03,275 --> 01:21:04,360
[on radio] This is Burns.

1315
01:21:04,443 --> 01:21:06,195
Tell them to bring an army.

1316
01:21:07,279 --> 01:21:09,239
[softly] Burns, we made
a terrible mistake.

1317
01:21:09,323 --> 01:21:10,616
Powell?

1318
01:21:10,699 --> 01:21:12,910
And thanks to our human allies,

1319
01:21:13,660 --> 01:21:15,746
I know just how to get the message home.

1320
01:21:16,288 --> 01:21:17,664
They're using our satellites.

1321
01:21:18,248 --> 01:21:19,625
They're calling an army.

1322
01:21:20,125 --> 01:21:21,251
They're gonna kill us all.

1323
01:21:22,211 --> 01:21:26,382
Thank you for your hospitality,
friend Powell.

1324
01:21:27,007 --> 01:21:28,467
He's all yours.

1325
01:21:29,718 --> 01:21:30,844
-No.
-[Agent Burns] Powell?

1326
01:21:30,969 --> 01:21:32,513
-[Dr. Powell] You have to stop them!
-Powell!

1327
01:21:32,596 --> 01:21:33,680
[ray gun powers up]

1328
01:21:34,765 --> 01:21:36,016
[both gasp]

1329
01:21:37,351 --> 01:21:38,727
[Ron] Where's the Krazy Glue?

1330
01:21:38,894 --> 01:21:41,021
What, did she cut the wire to the TV?

1331
01:21:41,563 --> 01:21:42,689
Ron.

1332
01:21:43,190 --> 01:21:45,067
[groans] Charlie!

1333
01:21:45,567 --> 01:21:46,735
Charlie!

1334
01:21:46,819 --> 01:21:49,947
[whirring] Nice!
Reel-to-reel still works.

1335
01:21:50,989 --> 01:21:52,324
Where is your sister?

1336
01:21:53,867 --> 01:21:55,119
Charlie's fallen ill

1337
01:21:55,202 --> 01:21:57,079
and must stay in her bedroom
for the rest of the evening.

1338
01:21:57,162 --> 01:21:58,789
She wishes not to be troubled.

1339
01:21:58,956 --> 01:22:00,290
Keep clear of her chambers.

1340
01:22:00,707 --> 01:22:01,750
What?

1341
01:22:04,586 --> 01:22:06,004
[swallows]

1342
01:22:06,088 --> 01:22:07,631
Charlie has fallen ill

1343
01:22:07,714 --> 01:22:10,551
and must stay in her bedroom
for the rest of the evening.

1344
01:22:10,676 --> 01:22:12,803
-She wishes not to...
-Otis!

1345
01:22:13,095 --> 01:22:15,013
Are you on drugs? Hmm?

1346
01:22:15,097 --> 01:22:16,557
No, no. Mom, Mom, Mom.

1347
01:22:16,640 --> 01:22:18,475
-Please stop. Stop!
-Charlie!

1348
01:22:18,600 --> 01:22:20,436
-Mom, there is no reason to go...
-Where is she?

1349
01:22:20,519 --> 01:22:22,563
-Mom, stop!
-Quit it, Otis.

1350
01:22:24,606 --> 01:22:25,941
[sighs]

1351
01:22:28,402 --> 01:22:29,653
Where is she?

1352
01:22:30,863 --> 01:22:32,072
Uh...

1353
01:22:33,282 --> 01:22:34,658
Otis?

1354
01:22:37,286 --> 01:22:39,580
[Shatter] I found a tower
to transmit our message.

1355
01:22:39,872 --> 01:22:41,832
-It's close.
-[electrical humming]

1356
01:22:41,915 --> 01:22:44,418
Oh. B-127.

1357
01:22:44,918 --> 01:22:46,462
I almost forgot.

1358
01:22:46,545 --> 01:22:47,838
I didn't.

1359
01:22:47,921 --> 01:22:49,006
[ray gun whirs]

1360
01:22:50,174 --> 01:22:51,592
No! Don't shoot!

1361
01:22:53,594 --> 01:22:54,887
[sobs] No!

1362
01:22:54,970 --> 01:22:56,972
[continues sobbing]

1363
01:23:10,402 --> 01:23:11,487
Bee!

1364
01:23:14,114 --> 01:23:15,240
Talk to me, Bee, talk to me.

1365
01:23:18,702 --> 01:23:20,496
[electricity crackling]

1366
01:23:22,331 --> 01:23:24,791
I can fix this. I can fix this.

1367
01:23:24,875 --> 01:23:26,668
[sobbing]

1368
01:23:29,004 --> 01:23:30,088
Charlie.

1369
01:23:30,172 --> 01:23:31,465
You got to wake up, Bee.

1370
01:23:31,840 --> 01:23:33,217
You got to wake up.

1371
01:23:33,509 --> 01:23:34,510
Please.

1372
01:23:34,927 --> 01:23:36,470
[sobbing]

1373
01:23:36,553 --> 01:23:38,013
Charlie, we got to go.

1374
01:23:42,809 --> 01:23:44,061
-[Charlie] The gun.
-What?

1375
01:23:44,144 --> 01:23:45,604
The electric gun. Get it.

1376
01:23:47,814 --> 01:23:49,149
I can fix you.

1377
01:23:51,944 --> 01:23:53,278
Come on, Bee.

1378
01:23:53,362 --> 01:23:54,738
Come back to me.

1379
01:24:00,953 --> 01:24:02,704
Come on, give me the other one.

1380
01:24:04,122 --> 01:24:05,499
[sniffles]

1381
01:24:09,127 --> 01:24:10,379
Bee, come on.

1382
01:24:12,839 --> 01:24:14,550
I can't lose you, too, Bee.

1383
01:24:15,092 --> 01:24:16,468
Please, Bee!

1384
01:24:19,471 --> 01:24:20,806
[sobs]

1385
01:24:28,564 --> 01:24:29,982
[Charlie sighs]

1386
01:24:30,607 --> 01:24:31,608
I'm sorry.

1387
01:24:45,789 --> 01:24:46,957
Oh.

1388
01:24:47,416 --> 01:24:48,625
[sobs]

1389
01:24:56,383 --> 01:24:57,467
Oh, my God.

1390
01:24:58,802 --> 01:25:00,804
Come on, Bee,
we've got to get you out of here.

1391
01:25:04,766 --> 01:25:06,476
-[visor whirring]
-[gasps]

1392
01:25:13,150 --> 01:25:15,861
[Memo] Charlie, there's like
a million guys out there!

1393
01:25:16,320 --> 01:25:18,196
-[Charlie grunts]
-We got to move, now.

1394
01:25:18,572 --> 01:25:20,490
Come on, Bee, you've gotta get up.
Can you get up?

1395
01:25:21,783 --> 01:25:23,327
There's a door in my way.

1396
01:25:26,038 --> 01:25:27,080
They've got bombs!

1397
01:25:27,164 --> 01:25:28,624
-We got to go.
-[Charlie] Bee, come on.

1398
01:25:30,626 --> 01:25:31,668
Charlie!

1399
01:25:31,752 --> 01:25:32,961
You've gotta get up, come on.

1400
01:25:33,837 --> 01:25:35,297
-Three.
-Charlie!

1401
01:25:35,714 --> 01:25:37,174
-Two.
-[Charlie] Come on.

1402
01:25:37,257 --> 01:25:38,300
One.

1403
01:25:38,383 --> 01:25:39,551
-Charlie!
-Come on.

1404
01:25:56,610 --> 01:25:57,778
Memo?

1405
01:26:01,031 --> 01:26:04,201
Memo. Memo, wake up.

1406
01:26:04,284 --> 01:26:05,702
[Memo coughs]

1407
01:26:05,786 --> 01:26:07,120
[Agent Burns] Easy.

1408
01:26:10,207 --> 01:26:11,083
Easy.

1409
01:26:13,835 --> 01:26:15,128
Hold your fire!

1410
01:26:15,629 --> 01:26:17,047
Get the kid out of here.

1411
01:26:18,757 --> 01:26:20,967
-Memo! Wake up, Memo!
-[Memo grunts]

1412
01:26:21,551 --> 01:26:22,678
[Agent Burns] Come on, kid.

1413
01:26:22,761 --> 01:26:24,221
Hey! No! [grunts]

1414
01:26:24,805 --> 01:26:25,847
Bee!

1415
01:26:26,139 --> 01:26:27,182
Run!

1416
01:26:27,265 --> 01:26:28,767
[both grunting]

1417
01:26:29,434 --> 01:26:30,435
Bee! [grunts]

1418
01:26:31,561 --> 01:26:32,646
Run!

1419
01:26:32,771 --> 01:26:34,690
-Let go of me!
-You need to get away from that thing.

1420
01:26:38,151 --> 01:26:40,070
-Take it down!
-[Charlie] No, stop!

1421
01:26:41,738 --> 01:26:42,698
Stop it!

1422
01:26:42,781 --> 01:26:44,408
[Agent Burns] Contain it and dismantle it!

1423
01:26:44,491 --> 01:26:46,159
Strip it down to parts!

1424
01:26:46,827 --> 01:26:47,911
[Charlie] Leave him alone!

1425
01:26:48,036 --> 01:26:49,454
You don't understand.

1426
01:26:49,538 --> 01:26:50,789
[whimpers]

1427
01:26:50,872 --> 01:26:52,207
Fight back, Bee!

1428
01:26:52,499 --> 01:26:53,875
-Bee!
-Kid, stop!

1429
01:26:53,959 --> 01:26:55,252
It's a machine!

1430
01:26:55,335 --> 01:26:57,379
He's more human than you'll ever be!

1431
01:26:57,462 --> 01:26:59,506
[grunts] That is enough!

1432
01:26:59,589 --> 01:27:00,882
[Charlie grunts]

1433
01:27:07,013 --> 01:27:08,223
[visor whirring]

1434
01:27:17,441 --> 01:27:18,859
[metal creaking]

1435
01:27:22,529 --> 01:27:23,572
Oh, shit.

1436
01:27:23,655 --> 01:27:25,198
[grunting]

1437
01:27:34,916 --> 01:27:35,959
[agent] Open fire!

1438
01:27:47,179 --> 01:27:48,680
[agents screaming]

1439
01:27:49,139 --> 01:27:51,099
Fall back! Take cover!

1440
01:27:59,983 --> 01:28:01,526
[agents screaming]

1441
01:28:01,610 --> 01:28:04,529
-[shots firing]
-[crashing]

1442
01:28:06,656 --> 01:28:07,616
Bee!

1443
01:28:10,327 --> 01:28:11,495
Bee!

1444
01:28:12,329 --> 01:28:13,789
[shots firing]

1445
01:28:13,872 --> 01:28:15,332
[Charlie] Bee, stop!

1446
01:28:29,805 --> 01:28:31,848
[breathing heavily]

1447
01:28:35,143 --> 01:28:37,312
You remember, don't you?

1448
01:28:38,188 --> 01:28:40,232
-[vehicle approaching]
-[gasps]

1449
01:28:42,067 --> 01:28:43,276
[Charlie] They're coming back.

1450
01:28:49,241 --> 01:28:50,450
[softly] Oh, God.

1451
01:28:51,076 --> 01:28:52,494
Are you okay?

1452
01:28:53,370 --> 01:28:55,372
Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.

1453
01:28:55,956 --> 01:28:57,582
We need to get out of here.

1454
01:28:59,000 --> 01:29:00,752
We've got to get you someplace safe.

1455
01:29:04,339 --> 01:29:05,966
Bee, stop. They will kill you!

1456
01:29:06,842 --> 01:29:09,219
[Optimus]
If the Decepticons find Earth,

1457
01:29:09,469 --> 01:29:12,222
then our people are truly finished.

1458
01:29:13,849 --> 01:29:16,101
[Charlie] Okay. Then we fight.

1459
01:29:24,568 --> 01:29:25,861
Let's go, get in.

1460
01:29:26,528 --> 01:29:28,530
[vehicle approaches]

1461
01:29:28,655 --> 01:29:30,574
Go on. I'll buy you
some time with these guys.

1462
01:29:31,825 --> 01:29:32,868
[chuckles]

1463
01:29:41,710 --> 01:29:42,961
You just kiss me?

1464
01:29:44,296 --> 01:29:45,463
On the cheek.

1465
01:29:45,714 --> 01:29:47,299
-Still counts.
-[car door closes]

1466
01:29:53,513 --> 01:29:54,514
Still counts.

1467
01:30:04,441 --> 01:30:05,442
Halt!

1468
01:30:06,943 --> 01:30:08,278
[stammers] Stop.

1469
01:30:08,361 --> 01:30:09,446
[horns honking]

1470
01:30:09,529 --> 01:30:10,572
[gasps]

1471
01:30:13,158 --> 01:30:14,492
Well, that didn't work.

1472
01:30:21,541 --> 01:30:22,626
[agent] Move, move!

1473
01:30:34,679 --> 01:30:36,222
[tires screeching]

1474
01:30:38,850 --> 01:30:40,602
Faster, Bee, faster!

1475
01:30:43,605 --> 01:30:45,127
We should really look
into getting seatbelts.

1476
01:30:45,252 --> 01:30:46,566
Oh, my God, oh, my God.

1477
01:30:46,650 --> 01:30:48,944
It's okay. She's gonna steal
the robot back, fight off the police,

1478
01:30:49,027 --> 01:30:50,820
kill two bigger robots,
and come right back home.

1479
01:30:50,904 --> 01:30:52,155
Shut up, Otis.

1480
01:30:52,656 --> 01:30:54,157
[reporter on radio]
Folks, this just breaking.

1481
01:30:54,324 --> 01:30:56,451
There appears to be
a high-speed chase underway

1482
01:30:56,534 --> 01:30:58,286
just outside McKinnon Air Base.

1483
01:30:58,370 --> 01:30:59,579
Go right! Go right!

1484
01:30:59,663 --> 01:31:00,705
-[tires squeal]
-[grunts]

1485
01:31:01,831 --> 01:31:03,249
[horns honking]

1486
01:31:04,501 --> 01:31:05,627
[pants]

1487
01:31:05,710 --> 01:31:07,128
[tires squeal]

1488
01:31:12,258 --> 01:31:14,386
Closer. Closer.

1489
01:31:14,469 --> 01:31:15,804
You lose that car,

1490
01:31:15,929 --> 01:31:17,597
I will personally rip your face off.

1491
01:31:18,181 --> 01:31:19,224
[tires screeching]

1492
01:31:21,059 --> 01:31:22,102
Oh, God!

1493
01:31:22,352 --> 01:31:23,478
It's all under control.

1494
01:31:25,605 --> 01:31:27,190
[horn honking]

1495
01:31:27,983 --> 01:31:29,776
-[Sally] Charlie!
-Mom?

1496
01:31:29,901 --> 01:31:31,736
You pull that car over right this second.

1497
01:31:31,820 --> 01:31:33,947
This is very unsafe, what you're doing.

1498
01:31:34,030 --> 01:31:35,740
Mom, you got to get out of here, okay?

1499
01:31:35,824 --> 01:31:37,742
-Whoa! Whoa!
-[horn honks]

1500
01:31:40,120 --> 01:31:41,121
[Charlie] Mom...

1501
01:31:41,413 --> 01:31:43,206
You have to trust me, please!

1502
01:31:44,666 --> 01:31:45,834
Charlie!

1503
01:31:45,917 --> 01:31:47,961
-We got to help her, Ron!
-Hang on.

1504
01:31:50,922 --> 01:31:52,590
Oh, my God! Ron!

1505
01:31:54,426 --> 01:31:55,927
[Agent Burns grunting]

1506
01:31:56,011 --> 01:31:57,721
Get out of the way!

1507
01:31:57,887 --> 01:31:59,889
Oh, my gosh! What are you doing?

1508
01:32:00,098 --> 01:32:02,017
I saw this on Miami Vice.

1509
01:32:04,936 --> 01:32:06,021
God!

1510
01:32:07,272 --> 01:32:09,691
-Oh. Oh. I got it, I got it, I got it.
-Oh, my God!

1511
01:32:09,774 --> 01:32:11,609
-[tires squeal]
-Whoa!

1512
01:32:13,069 --> 01:32:14,571
[horn blaring]

1513
01:32:16,614 --> 01:32:18,199
[horn beeping]

1514
01:32:18,283 --> 01:32:19,826
-[gasps]
-[brakes screech]

1515
01:32:19,909 --> 01:32:20,994
Whoa!

1516
01:32:21,077 --> 01:32:22,662
[brakes screech]

1517
01:32:25,665 --> 01:32:26,833
[Agent Burns] Whoa!

1518
01:32:27,375 --> 01:32:28,835
[all screaming]

1519
01:32:33,965 --> 01:32:35,216
Nice driving, Ron.

1520
01:32:38,011 --> 01:32:39,471
[breathes heavily]
Is everyone okay?

1521
01:32:40,096 --> 01:32:42,849
Ron! We have a kid in the car!

1522
01:32:43,099 --> 01:32:45,852
I was trying to save
the other kid! What was I--

1523
01:32:45,935 --> 01:32:47,353
It was a lose-lose.

1524
01:32:47,604 --> 01:32:50,190
Otis? Otis, are you all right?

1525
01:32:51,691 --> 01:32:52,776
That...

1526
01:32:53,568 --> 01:32:54,819
was radical.

1527
01:33:02,994 --> 01:33:04,829
[trilling]

1528
01:33:14,255 --> 01:33:16,716
[energy pulsating]

1529
01:33:22,305 --> 01:33:24,641
Preparing satellites
to transmit our message.

1530
01:33:43,910 --> 01:33:45,829
Okay. What's the plan?

1531
01:33:50,500 --> 01:33:51,876
This is the plan?

1532
01:33:52,710 --> 01:33:53,837
I hate this plan.

1533
01:33:54,045 --> 01:33:55,255
Bee, I want to help.

1534
01:33:55,338 --> 01:33:56,506
[radio warbles]

1535
01:33:56,589 --> 01:34:01,010
♪ I would hate anything
To happen to her ♪

1536
01:34:01,219 --> 01:34:02,804
You're actually talking.

1537
01:34:03,263 --> 01:34:05,306
And you're listening to The Smiths.

1538
01:34:15,483 --> 01:34:16,609
Be careful.

1539
01:34:18,278 --> 01:34:19,696
[visor whirring]

1540
01:34:25,702 --> 01:34:28,788
Handle him!
And finish the job this time!

1541
01:34:29,789 --> 01:34:30,999
[helicopter blades whirring]

1542
01:34:40,216 --> 01:34:41,801
[Dropkick grunting]

1543
01:34:45,471 --> 01:34:46,472
Oh, shit!

1544
01:34:49,809 --> 01:34:51,394
[grunting]

1545
01:35:00,486 --> 01:35:02,363
[both grunting]

1546
01:35:14,042 --> 01:35:15,668
How the hell am I gonna get up there?

1547
01:35:15,752 --> 01:35:17,754
[crashing]

1548
01:35:21,007 --> 01:35:22,675
[both grunting]

1549
01:35:31,851 --> 01:35:33,770
[metal clattering]

1550
01:35:35,271 --> 01:35:36,439
[Charlie yells]

1551
01:35:40,193 --> 01:35:41,194
[gasps]

1552
01:35:42,946 --> 01:35:44,572
[screaming]

1553
01:35:56,459 --> 01:35:58,294
[both grunting]

1554
01:36:19,857 --> 01:36:20,858
[Dropkick groaning]

1555
01:36:30,868 --> 01:36:32,287
[Charlie grunts]

1556
01:36:37,333 --> 01:36:38,334
[beeping]

1557
01:36:44,465 --> 01:36:45,550
[gasps]

1558
01:36:45,633 --> 01:36:47,635
[helicopter blades whirring]

1559
01:36:50,972 --> 01:36:53,057
There. The one on the tower.

1560
01:36:56,227 --> 01:36:57,603
-[groans]
-[gasps]

1561
01:36:57,687 --> 01:36:59,022
[shots firing]

1562
01:37:00,189 --> 01:37:01,691
[Charlie whimpering]

1563
01:37:27,842 --> 01:37:29,802
[both grunting]

1564
01:37:31,471 --> 01:37:32,680
[tires screeching]

1565
01:37:53,451 --> 01:37:55,745
You think these little chains can hold...

1566
01:38:06,339 --> 01:38:07,965
[helicopter blades whirring]

1567
01:38:08,341 --> 01:38:09,384
Okay.

1568
01:38:17,600 --> 01:38:18,601
[grunts]

1569
01:38:20,144 --> 01:38:21,187
[grunts]

1570
01:38:23,689 --> 01:38:24,816
[grunts]

1571
01:38:27,068 --> 01:38:28,403
[grunting]

1572
01:38:34,742 --> 01:38:36,244
Hold on!

1573
01:38:37,787 --> 01:38:39,163
[grunting]

1574
01:38:42,708 --> 01:38:43,751
[grunts]

